 in the way we look at work, and it \u2019 s made possible thanks in large part to advances in technologies such as remote storage and remote desktop software.\nRemote desktop storage has become an important tool for digital nomads.\nWith it, they can access their work computer or office network from anywhere in the world as long as they have an internet connection.\nThis ability to work remotely not only provides flexibility, but also allows digital nomads to maintain high levels of productivity wherever they are.\nSplashtop understands the complexity of this lifestyle and is committed to providing solutions to address the unique challenges faced by digital travelers, such as connectivity issues and secure access to remote resources.\nWe strive to improve the flexibility provided by this lifestyle, aiming to make the world a seamless workspace.\nWith the right remote desktop and remote storage tools, the world can indeed be your workplace.\nThat \u2019 s the power of technology today \u2013 it makes geography irrelevant, it \u2019 s changing the way we work, travel and live.\nWelcome to the digital nomadic world powered by Splashtop \u2019 s remote desktop solutions.\nDefining digital nomads and their challenges\nDigital nomadism is the practice of doing work by relying on digital technology, often for remote work from abroad.\nThis lifestyle offers enticing benefits such as flexibility, freedom and the charm of travel.\nHowever, this is not without challenges.\nThe key is connectivity issues due to different global internet stability and maintaining productivity in different time zones and environments.\nThe right tools, including reliable remote desktop software, can help address these challenges and make digital nomadic a rewarding and efficient way to work.\nRemote Desktop: Solutions for Digital Travellers\nRemote desktop software bridges the connection between your device and computer by using the Internet as a medium.\nThis process involves using two applications, even the \"client\" application on the portable device and the \"proxy\" application installed on the desktop.\nThis duo enables you to establish a remote desktop connection that effectively lets you control and interact with your desktop, regardless of time and place, as if you were immersive.\nBasically, you can control your primary computer, access files, use apps, and even perform complex tasks from a remote location, all as if you were sitting in front of your computer.\nDigital nomads can leverage remote desktop technology to dramatically increase their productivity.\nFor example, let \u2019 s say you \u2019 re a digital hobbyist who often uses specialized software installed on your home computer.\nWith remote desktop storage, you can use your laptop or even tablet to run this software from anywhere in the world without having to carry your home computer with you.\nAlternatively, you may be a software developer or graphic designer (and also a digital nomad!) and you may need access to a powerful home desktop for coding or testing.\nBy using remote desktop software, you can take advantage of the processing power of your home computer to run intensive applications smoothly while traveling from a portable laptop or even tablet.\nAs a digital hobbyist, you may be worried that the main computer in your home is going into sleep mode, which may interrupt your remote storage.\nThis can interfere with your workflow, especially if you are in a different time zone or location.\nHowever, with Splashtop, this concern is a thing of the past. Splashtop offers a \u201cWake Up Computer \u201d feature specifically designed to wake your remote computer from its sleep state.\nThis feature ensures that you can always connect to your computer, no matter where you are in the world, providing an uninterrupted, reliable remote storage experience.\nRemote desktop tools also provide secure access to your files without the need to sync or transfer them across devices, reducing the risk of data loss or theft.\nThis technology is also beneficial when digital nomads need to collaborate with team members in real time, as they can remotely access a colleague \u2019 s computer to get help or perform a task.\nOne of the major benefits that remote desktop storage brings to digital travelers is the ability to overcome the unpredictability of travel.\nWhether it \u2019 s an unforeseen situation that causes a hardware failure, or simply an inability to access a specific document, a remote desktop solution can provide the necessary buffers to keep your workflow running smoothly.\nOne such solution is Splashtop, which is designed to provide secure and reliable remote storage. With a user-friendly interface and strong connectivity, Splashtop supports a seamless remote work experience.\nIt is an effective tool for connecting to your main computer from any other device (laptop, tablet or even smartphone).\nIts cross-platform features allow you to work across operating systems without compatibility issues.\nAll of this doesn \u2019 t require a lot of technical setup. All you need is an internet connection.\nWith Splashtop or similar tools, the world truly becomes a workspace for digital hobbyists, making geography a consideration of the past.\nTips for Using Remote Desktop Storage Effectively\nChoosing the right remote desktop tool is critical to getting the benefits of this technology.\nWhen choosing a tool, consider factors such as ease of use, reliability, speed, and security features.\nCompatibility with different operating systems and devices is also an important factor, especially for digital nomads who may use various devices.\nEnsuring safe and smooth remote storage is just as important.\nFind tools that provide robust security measures such as two-factor authentication and data encryption.\nA reliable internet connection also plays a vital role in ensuring smooth access.\nIt is recommended to use backup connection options in case of network instability, such as portable Wi-Fi or mobile hotspots.\nWith Splashtop \u2019 s adaptive streaming technology, you can still experience high-performance remote storage even on less than perfect internet connections, ensuring a seamless digital nomadic experience.\nWith Splashtop Remote Desktop Software, you will be able to...\n\u2022 Work from home or anywhere in the world by accessing your work computer from any device without having to worry about transferring data to the cloud or investing in additional hardware or software licenses.\n\u2022 Experience real-time, high-definition viewing of a remote computer screen, delivering up to 4K streaming at 40 frames per second for a low-latency remote storage experience.\nControl your computer remotely from another computer, tablet, or mobile device as if you were sitting directly in front of it.\n\u2022 Direct access and modification of any document on a remote computer without cloud upload or email transfer.\n\u2022 Operate any software on a remote computer, from Adobe Creative Suite and video editing applications to CAD programs and much more.\nSecurity is a top priority at Splashtop, and we protect your and your company \u2019 s data with encrypted connections, multi-level password options, two-factor authentication, and other features.\nLearn more about Splashtop \u2019 s security and sign up for a free trial to experience it for yourself!\nConclusion \u2013 Remote Desktop for Digital Nomads\nEmbracing the digital nomadic lifestyle requires versatile tools to meet the unique challenges of remote work.\nRemote desktop storage is an indispensable tool that increases flexibility and ensures productivity no matter where you are.\nIt allows you to access and control your main computer from a remote location, use specific software, and securely access your files.\nTools like Splashtop provide a seamless remote work experience that digital hobbyists anywhere in the world can rely on.\nBy offering a combination of strong connectivity, cross-platform compatibility, security features, and high-performance streaming, Splashtop is the ideal companion for digital hobbyists, hybrid workers, and remote workers.\nReady to unleash your full potential as a digital nomad?\nLearn more about Splashtop \u2019 s remote desktop software and discover how it can revolutionize your remote work experience.\nSign up for a free trial now!\nVerena Cooper\nVerena is an International SEO Manager at Splashtop.\nFree Trial\nRelated Content\nCustomer focus\nThis Week \u2019 s Featured Comments\nIn-depth knowledge\nCompare\nScaling Alternatives to Remote IT Support\nIn-depth knowledge\nRemote Learning and Education\nDemo video: Using Chromebooks to remotely access Windows and Mac computers\nIn-depth knowledge\nRemote Learning and Education\nSolve online education challenges with remote access and document security software\nIn-depth knowledge\nView All Blogs\nWe'd love to hear from you.\nContact Us\nGet the latest Splashtop news and special offers\nSubscribe Now\n\u2022 Standard Specification\n\u2022 Privacy Policy\n\u2022 Terms of Use\nCopyright \u00a9 2023 Splashtop Inc.\nAll rights reserved.\n$Prices shown are in USD","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0018.json.gz:4164","uncompressed_offset":37536649,"url":"www.splashtop.com/tw/blog/remote-desktop-for-digital-nomads","warc_date":"2023-06-18T06:22:01.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:b67cd69f-4c83-4193-99ab-2cc0767b6bfd>","warc_url":"https://www.splashtop.com/tw/blog/remote-desktop-for-digital-nomads"},"created":"2023-06-18T06:25:46.000Z","lang":"eng"},"ec9e942a-2b47-4552-9825-4e206606823c_696735006":{"id":"ec9e942a-2b47-4552-9825-4e206606823c_696735006","text":"\nJapan's 'Digital Nomad Visa' Up For Grabs In March From Who Can Apply To Eligibility, Here's All You Need To Know\n\n\n(MENAFN- Live Mint) \"Japan is set to launch a digital nomad visa in March that will allow citizens of 49 countries to stay in the nation for up to six months serves as the best place to combine work and travel considering its metropolitan cities, diverse natural landscapes and world-renowned pop culture. In a move to boost the tourism industry and its economy and international competitiveness, the island country is increasingly opening up to foreigners read: 'With current service, visas can be issued in very short time to Indian citizens': German envoyFind out who can apply for Japan's digital nomad visaJapan's digital nomad visa will be available to citizens of 49 countries and territories. These eligible nations are those that have signed a tax treaty with the country or are visa-exempt when visiting Japan. The list of eligible nations includes all EU countries, Armenia, Belarus, Georgia, Iceland, Liechtenstein, Moldova, Monaco, North Macedonia, Norway, Serbia, Switzerland, Turkey and the United Kingdom, reported Euronews. However, as of now, India is not on the list read: Visa, Mastercard to stop card-based B2B payments via third party fintech platforms: SourcesOne must work for an employer or corporation outside of the host nation or own a business that can be managed from anywhere in the world to be eligible for this visa. The visa mainly targets IT professionals as well as highly skilled professionals. This visa is expected to apply to YouTubers as well who make revenue from overseas advertisers read: US visa news: H-1B, L-1 and EB-5 visa fees hiked; to come into effect from 1 April. Check details hereThis East Asian country is threatened by its ageing population and hence faced with a high dependency ratio. According to Japan's labour ministry, over two million foreign nationals work in the country currently, which is the highest number ever recorded much does one need to earn to be eligible?To qualify for Japan's digital nomad visa, applicants must earn at least 10 million Japanese Yen (\u20ac62,672) annually and have private health insurance coverage, reported Euronews read: VFS Global expects visa processing time to ease this yearMoreover, family members including children and spouses will be allowed to accompany digital nomads during their stay in Japan but they also have to be covered by private medical insurance read: Schengen visa fee hike: Here's how costly your trip to Europe can getDigital nomads are 45 per cent more productive than their office-based counterparts, according to a US study. It was also found that these digital nomads are happier, with 91 per cent reporting job satisfaction and flexibility as the primary benefits countries including Portugal, Canada, and Germany, have introduced digital nomad visas and modified laws to promote working tourism. Dedicated remote working centres have emerged over the years that offer individuals the freedom to choose their workplace including beachside locations.\n\nMENAFN16022024007365015876ID1107862125\n\n\nLegal Disclaimer:\nMENAFN provides the information \u201cas is\u201d without warranty of any kind. We do not accept any responsibility or liability for the accuracy, content, images, videos, licenses, completeness, legality, or reliability of the information contained in this article. If you have any complaints or copyright issues related to this article, kindly contact the provider above.","url":"https://menafn.com/1107862125/Japans-Digital-Nomad-Visa-Up-For-Grabs-In-March-From-Who-Can-Apply-To-Eligibility-Heres-All-You-Need-To-Know"},"088e0346-91bf-43fd-b68c-748ae1e1247f_998032520":{"id":"088e0346-91bf-43fd-b68c-748ae1e1247f_998032520","text":"Malaysia hops on to digital-nomad visa bandwagon\n\nAt lakefront of the Malaysia's administrative center, Putrajaya. (File photo: Reuters)\nMUMBAI: Want to chill out on Malaysian beaches without taking leave from work? Well, this country is the latest to jump on to the bandwagon with its offering of a digital-nomad pass.\nIt joins countries as varied as Estonia, Malta, Bahamas, Cyprus, Thailand and many others, which following the pandemic have opened up their doors to digital nomads \u2013 people who work remotely but from another country. However, tax and other regulatory issues, both for the employer and the individual need to be borne in mind, before moving to these exotic locations.\nFrom October 1, the Malaysian government has begun to accept online applications for the newly introduced digital nomad pass, termed as the \u2018DE Rantau Nomad Pass Program\u2019. Eligible foreign nationals whose annual income is over $ 24,000 can apply and can stay in Malaysia with their dependents for up to three to 12 months initially, with an option to extend for another year. This is a multiple-entry programme, unlike tourist visa, which is a single entry scheme with a validity of just three months. The applicant has to submit proof of work or employment and pay the requisite fees.\nFOLLOW US ON SOCIAL MEDIA\nFacebookTwitterInstagramKOO APPYOUTUBE\nStart a Conversation\nend of article","url":"https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/nri/other-news/malaysia-hops-on-to-digital-nomad-visa-bandwagon/articleshow/94923931.cms"},"f9238697-72e5-45a4-88bd-8504c4016eba_427630041":{"id":"f9238697-72e5-45a4-88bd-8504c4016eba_427630041","text":"Digital Nomad Visa Programs: An APAC Update\n\nK\nKlasko\n\nContributor\n\nKlasko Immigration Law Partners is dedicated to providing industry-leading employment-based, investment-based, and litigation immigration services to our clients. We help our clients achieve their goals by providing comprehensive immigration legal services. We have a reputation for creative solutions to difficult immigration problems through cutting-edge strategies. Our clients value our extreme responsiveness and our innovative, practical, and effective immigration strategies.\nDigital nomad visa programs have grown increasingly popular. Seen as a means of attracting top-tier, global talent and tax revenue, this trend is especially prevalent in the Asian Pacific region.\nUnited States Employment and HR\nTo print this article, all you need is to be registered or login on Mondaq.com.\n\nDigital nomad visa programs have grown increasingly popular. Seen as a means of attracting top-tier, global talent and tax revenue, this trend is especially prevalent in the Asian Pacific region. Indeed, Japan recently announced it joined the digital nomad visa party \u2013 its policy to be officially rolled out in early April 2024. Below, we discuss this new development and provide a summary of the current state of digital nomad programs in the APAC region.\n\nJapan's new digital nomad visa program: a sumo-sized development\n\nJapan's Ministry of Justice announced that Japan created a digital nomad visa. Situated as the 4th largest economy in the world, Japan began issuing digital nomad visas at the beginning of April 2024 to the citizens of 50 countries and territories.\n\nThe short-list of eligible countries includes at least the United States, Australia, and Singapore. The visas are valid for up to six months and available to those earning more than \u00a510 million (app. $68,300) per year. Nomads may work from anywhere in the country and bring their spouses and children with them. Their work must be tied to \"a sales contract or non-provision contract...with a public or private company in a foreign country\". Carrying private health insurance will be obligatory to participate in the program.\n\nBehind only China and Thailand, Japan is consistently ranked as one of the largest recipients of international visitors in APAC. In 2024 alone, it is forecasted that Japan will receive a total of 33.1 million visitors. With the aperture of this new program, coupled with sustained global interest in Japan's rich cultural heritage, the country is projected to receive thousands of digital nomads for years to come.\n\nThai-tanic-sized companies are welcomed in the Kingdom\n\nVisa options for digital nomads in Thailand remain limited. Whereas the B visa program allows visitors to enter the Kingdom for up to 90 days to engage in a short list of activities, the government has gone to greater lengths to attract international corporate investment.\n\nIndeed, under its \"Remote Workers for Well-Established Overseas Companies\" program, employees of publicly traded companies (or private companies with combined revenue of over $150 million in the last three years) will be able to apply for a 10-year long resident permit. The employee must (i) make an annual salary of at least $80,000.00 USD per year for two consecutive years or (ii) if holding a master's degree, make no less than $40,000 USD for the last two years. Alternatively, the individual may be self-employed provided they own productive intellectual property or have received Series A funding of no less than $1 million USD. Like Japan, visa applicants must carry personal health insurance.\n\nWith some of the lowest corporate tax rates in all of APAC, Thailand is situating itself as one of the region's premier hotbeds for foreign investment and, consequently, international talent.\n\nMalaysia welcomes entrepreneurs from backgrounds as diverse as their landscapes\n\nMaylasia arguably presents one of the most agile digital nomad visa programs in APAC. Offering temporary residence through the \"De Rantau Nomad\" program, employees of local or foreign employers, freelancers, and independent contractors are welcome. The nomad must be coming to work in an IT or digital space and earn at least $24,000 USD per year.\n\nPursuing a K-drama storyline in South Korea remains tricky\n\nEarly this year, South Korea made a splash on the global stage by launching its own version of a digital nomad visa: the \"Workcation\" visa. Whereas the visa program does offer a two-year period of validity, it is available only under a niche set of circumstances. For example, the minimum income threshold is KRW 85,000,000, or approximately $63,683.53. Digital nomads availing themselves must not only refrain from assuming gainful employment in South Korea, but must also refrain from earning money in South Korea associated with the South Korean economy (e.g., entering contracts with local businesses). In addition to having at least one year of work experience, nomads must also carry health insurance coverage valued at KRW 100 million, or about $75,000 USD. Given these restrictions, we anticipate S. Korea's digital nomad visa program to be leveraged only by the truest of K-POP fans.\n\nThe content of this article is intended to provide a general guide to the subject matter. Specialist advice should be sought about your specific circumstances.\n\nDigital Nomad Visa Programs: An APAC Update\n\nUnited States Employment and HR\n\nContributor\n\nKlasko Immigration Law Partners is dedicated to providing industry-leading employment-based, investment-based, and litigation immigration services to our clients. We help our clients achieve their goals by providing comprehensive immigration legal services. We have a reputation for creative solutions to difficult immigration problems through cutting-edge strategies. Our clients value our extreme responsiveness and our innovative, practical, and effective immigration strategies.\nSee More Popular Content From\n\nMondaq uses cookies on this website. By using our website you agree to our use of cookies as set out in our Privacy Policy.\n\nLearn More","url":"https://www.mondaq.com:443/unitedstates/employment-and-hr/1469128/digital-nomad-visa-programs-an-apac-update"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T146","run_id":"dog","topic_id":"1006","task":"multilingual","request_id":"1006","narrative_id":"1006"},"responses":[{"citations":{"ea90bb4e-0607-4636-afd5-5e325bcbfef8_77576442":1.0},"text":"The digital nomad lifestyle is a growing trend where individuals work remotely and travel frequently, often using laptops and stable internet connections to perform their jobs from anywhere in the world."},{"citations":{"ea90bb4e-0607-4636-afd5-5e325bcbfef8_77576442":1.0},"text":"This lifestyle has become increasingly popular, with many countries introducing specific visas to support digital nomads, including Dubai, Iceland, and Mexico."},{"citations":{"ea90bb4e-0607-4636-afd5-5e325bcbfef8_77576442":1.0},"text":"In fact, over 50 countries now offer visas for digital nomads, making it easier for them to work and travel abroad."},{"citations":{"ea90bb4e-0607-4636-afd5-5e325bcbfef8_77576442":1.0},"text":"However, the requirements for these visas can be strict, with some countries requiring proof of savings or income, such as Mexico, which requires $43,000 in savings, or Portugal, which requires a monthly income of at least $4,500."},{"citations":{"ea90bb4e-0607-4636-afd5-5e325bcbfef8_77576442":1.0},"text":"Indonesia, on the other hand, requires digital nomads to have more than $200,000 in savings, but allows them to engage in \"investment and other activities\"."},{"citations":{"ea90bb4e-0607-4636-afd5-5e325bcbfef8_77576442":1.0},"text":"Despite these requirements, many digital nomads use tourist visas to enter countries and work remotely, with 3,000 foreigners entering Indonesia on B211A tourist visas for telecommuting between January and September last year."},{"citations":{"ea90bb4e-0607-4636-afd5-5e325bcbfef8_77576442":1.0},"text":"The rise of digital nomadism is driven by factors such as the increase in high-speed internet and freelancing, as well as declining home ownership and marriage rates."},{"citations":{"ea90bb4e-0607-4636-afd5