ty and performance."}],"references":["9e893a13-a5bb-4822-8f87-187cba831d3d_453477269","cd6f7c06-5e22-4103-9de2-9817a9a60efa_121885815","7662ae65-98c5-4a3f-9b24-83a5f9fb7a72_115461755","82c7d54c-fbec-441a-91f2-7aca1b82742c_1008363996"],"documents":{"9e893a13-a5bb-4822-8f87-187cba831d3d_453477269":{"id":"9e893a13-a5bb-4822-8f87-187cba831d3d_453477269","text":"Russia \u2019 s poor performance on the Ukrainian battlefield has become a global laughingstock, and it is expected that Russia, as an arms exporter, will lose a large number of orders and turn to China.\nAs a matter of fact, the Russian-Ukrainian war is still at a stalemate, and the old Russian military customer, Sudan, an Islamic state in North Africa, has decided to buy the J-10C fighter that China has strongly promoted in recent years. If the two sides are determined, Sudan will be the second customer of China's J-10C export after Pakistan.\nTurkish media International Defense Analysis (IDA) recently reported the news, but did not specify the amount and price of the purchase, which may be that the details of the sales contract are still under negotiation.\nIf the price of export to Pakistan is estimated at 40 million US dollars, the price of Sudan's purchase may be higher, because Pakistan's order is the first order of J-10C export, the price is naturally more favorable, and now Sudan's purchase to China is mainly Russia's image destruction, not the price factor; The aim is to counter India \u2019 s established French Tornado fighter, US-made F-16 and Indian Su-30MKI, but Sudan does not currently have this need, and may only be equipped with the shorter range PL-10, but this part may have little impact on the price.\nAt the beginning of this year, Pakistan officially released the news of the purchase of J-10C, there are unconfirmed rumors that J-10C may appear in Africa a second customer, which is more likely to be Sudan, and the purchase of the model will not be J-10C, the cooperation between China and Pakistan JF-17 Dragon is also one of the options, after all, JF-17 uses more customers.\nWith an area of nearly 2 million square kilometers, the Islamic state of Sudan in North Africa is the third largest country in Africa. Its name Sudan means \"black land\" in official Arabic.\nSudan, ruled by a military government, has long been plagued by the Darfur conflict and South Sudan's independence, and has been named the \"most unstable country in the world\".\nEconomically based on agricultural and animal husbandry processing products, the military has long been supported by the former Soviet Union and Russia, and the existing weapons are mostly Russian-Chinese systems, and there are a small number of US-French weapons.\nThe aircraft purchased from China and Russia are mostly old models, such as China's Keang-5, J-7, FTC-2000, etc. The Russian-made MiG-23, MiG-29, Su-24, Su-25, etc., a total of about 40 ~ 50 aircraft.\nThe FTC-2000, also known as the Jian-9, is considered to be the third generation trainer, so there has been a need to update the fighter fleet for many years.\nFrom the perspective of the composition of the Sudanese Air Force, it is still the largest number of Russian-made fighters, so it is the most likely to buy Russian-made fighters again.\nAlthough the French surge is also actively in contact, the price of each aircraft is as high as 100 to 200 million US dollars to deter the sultan.\nSince this year, the Russian Air Force and fighter aircraft have shown everyone \u2019 s surprise, which has seriously hit the outside world \u2019 s perception of Russian-made military fire, so the J-10C seized the opportunity as early as the contact, although it has not yet achieved actual combat results, but also Pakistan began to use on the tense India-Pakistan border, there are not many buyers in the international search, in the current atmosphere, the J-10C deal is finally Get a breakthrough.\nThe size of Sudan's air force is small, if the first batch of J-10C is purchased, the number should only be more than 10, about enough to form a squadron.\nIn recent years, China has pushed J-10C internationally, and many countries have expressed interest. In addition to Thailand in Southeast Asia and Argentina in South America, some countries in the Middle East and Africa have also been considered.\nEspecially after Russia \u2019 s performance in Ukraine has become an international laughingstock, many customers who used Russian-made aircraft in the past should turn to China.\nIn addition to fighter aircraft, other ground weapons or various types of frigates, unmanned ships and now the most popular drones, will also be due to the performance of the Russian army and China get a large number of orders.\nSince fighter trading has always been the largest trading item in the international arms market, if China \u2019 s J-10C can have a big win in this wave of Russian orders, it will significantly boost China \u2019 s ranking in the global arms market share.\nAccording to the 2021 ranking of the Stockholm International Peace Research Institute, the United States ranked first in arms transactions for the year with 39%, Russia ranked second with 19%, France ranked third with 11%, and China ranked fourth with 4.9%.\nAnd France \u2019 s share of the increase mainly comes from India and the Middle East countries to buy surge fighters, China J-10C this year has Pakistan \u2019 s deal, if coupled with Sudan \u2019 s order, it may surpass France to become the world \u2019 s fourth largest arms exporter in 2022, if the J-10C can thus open the market, and even in a few years may surpass Russia, to become only the United States defense industrial power.\nSource: Headlines Revealed on Facebook.com\n# J-10C # SUDAN # JET # ARMY # RUSSIA","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2022-0032.json.gz:1865","uncompressed_offset":453477269,"url":"www.chinatimes.com/realtimenews/20221027000680-260407","warc_date":"2022-10-26T21:22:26.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:9e893a13-a5bb-4822-8f87-187cba831d3d>","warc_url":"https://www.chinatimes.com/realtimenews/20221027000680-260407"},"created":"2022-10-26T21:41:50.000Z","lang":"eng"},"cd6f7c06-5e22-4103-9de2-9817a9a60efa_121885815":{"id":"cd6f7c06-5e22-4103-9de2-9817a9a60efa_121885815","text":"Adsence Ads 300X250\nAdsense Ads 900\u00d7250\n\nPAF formally inducts Rafale rival China-made J-10C fighter jets\n\nWeb Desk BOL News\n\n11th Mar, 2022. 02:25 pm\nAdsense Ads 300 x 100\nAdsence Ads 300X250\n\nKAMRA: The Pakistan Air Force (PAF) formally inducted a modern Chinese-made J-10C multi-role combat aircraft also known as \u201cvigorous dragon\u201d during a ceremony held at Kamra Airbase on Friday.\n\nPrime Minister Imran Khan attended the induction ceremony of the single-engine fighter jet at the invitation of Chief of the Air Staff (CAS) Air Chief Marshal Zaheer Ahmad Babar, along with other federal ministers and the Chinese ambassador.\n\nDuring the ceremony, The Prime Minister has witnessed a thrilling flypast of various aircraft formations, including the newly inducted J10C, F-16s, JF-17s, and Mirages, which displayed a sophisticated array of avionics and weaponry.\n\nRead more:\u00a0PAF\u2019s acquisition of J10-C\n\nFollowing the flypast, the Prime Minister witnessed the landing of five J-10C aircraft, which have been inducted into the 15 Squadron.\n\nThe J-10C is larger and can be outfitted with a bigger active electronically scanned array (AESA) radar than the JF-17 Block 3 uses.\n\nThe aircraft can carry fourth-generation air-to-air missiles such as the short-range PL-10 and the beyond-visual-range PL-15.\n\nAccording to a foreign media report, China will deliver a total of 25 J-10C fighter jets to Pakistan, significantly increasing the country\u2019s military capability to defend airspace.\n\nRead more:\u00a0J-10C induction ceremony: Pakistan knows how to protect its boundaries, says Imran\n\nAfter being tested in Chengdu, the first batch of combat aircraft arrived in Pakistan a few days ago.\n\nImages of a Pakistan Air Force (PAF) J-10C fighter jet with the Pakistan Air Force (PAF) markings recently surfaced on social media and were widely circulated by media outlets.\n\nChinese analysts have praised the latest defence cooperation between China and Pakistan, saying that the move is significant for both countries because it strengthens the Pakistani military\u2019s combat capabilities, promotes China\u2019s aviation equipment, and serves regional security interests.\n\n\u201cThe J-10C will significantly improve the Pakistan Air Force\u2019s combat capabilities,\u201d Chinese analysts predicted.\n\n\u201cThe J-10C is a 4.5-generation medium-sized fighter jet that is more powerful than the China-Pakistan jointly developed lightweight fighter jet, the JF-17, which is currently in service with the Pakistan Air Force,\u201d Shi Hong, Executive Chief Editor of Shipborne Weapons, told the Global Times.\n\n\nDownload BOL News App for latest news","url":"https://www.bolnews.com/pakistan/2022/03/paf-formally-inducts-rafale-rival-china-made-j-10c-fighter-jets/"},"7662ae65-98c5-4a3f-9b24-83a5f9fb7a72_115461755":{"id":"7662ae65-98c5-4a3f-9b24-83a5f9fb7a72_115461755","text":"Turkey replaces F-16 with Chinese fighter jet\nWednesday 08 March 2023 - 12: 09 GMT\nKagri Erhan, a member of the Security Council and Foreign Policy of the Turkish Presidency, announced that Ankara is expected to abandon its requests for American-made fourth-generation F-16C / D fighter jets due to the availability of a better alternative.\nWorld - Turkey\nThe Turkish official noted that the \u201c$20 billion cost package \u201d and the availability of more cost-effective options, notably the Chinese J-10C, could make such a rollout a reality.\n\"Now we have other options such as the Chinese plane that was sold to Pakistan, the Russian planes and also the Eurofighter,\" he said.\nAccording to Miltary Watch, Pakistan began receiving Chinese J-10C fighters in February 2022.\nThe Chinese fighter is of the same weight as its American counterpart, the F-16, but it is several decades newer with multiple features and performance advantages, especially in terms of armament, flight and flight performance.\nIt is a lightweight single-engine fighter with low operating cost and improved fifth-generation avionics.\nChinese aircraft also have similar capabilities and in most respects are superior to their American counterparts, in addition to requiring less maintenance needs and much faster delivery time.\nAlthough Turkey is the largest foreign operator of the US F-16, with about 250 in service, which means the new aircraft can be easily integrated with existing training and logistics systems and weapons, China has in the past modified its fighters to be able to operate US weapons at the request of foreign customers.\nOne of the main advantages of the Chinese fighter is its very low cost compared to its American counterpart, due to the fact that China manufactures large quantities of them, unlike the American.\nTurkey \u2019 s preference for lightweight fighters makes the Chinese single-engine aircraft an effective and pioneering option.","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0007.json.gz:10313","uncompressed_offset":115461755,"url":"www.alalam.ir/news/6559603/%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%83%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%A8%D8%AF%D9%84-%D8%A5%D9%81-16-%D8%A8%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%84%D8%A9-%D8%B5%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%8A%D8%A9","warc_date":"2023-03-08T12:32:32.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:7662ae65-98c5-4a3f-9b24-83a5f9fb7a72>","warc_url":"https://www.alalam.ir/news/6559603/%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%83%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%A8%D8%AF%D9%84-%D8%A5%D9%81-16-%D8%A8%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%84%D8%A9-%D8%B5%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%8A%D8%A9"},"created":"2023-03-08T12:37:13.000Z","lang":"eng"},"82c7d54c-fbec-441a-91f2-7aca1b82742c_1008363996":{"id":"82c7d54c-fbec-441a-91f2-7aca1b82742c_1008363996","text":"US newspaper lists Su-35 and MiG-31 on list of five most dangerous fighter jets\nScience and Technology\nThe Su-35 fighter.\nCopy Link https: / / www.rt.com / t1a7\nMilitary Watch lists Su-35 and MiG-31 as the five most dangerous fighters for the U.S. Air Force.\nJ-20\nThe list included the Chinese J-20, which became the second fifth-generation aircraft after the American F-35, and was designed to enable the fighter to fly at supersonic speed without operating the Forsage.\nMiG-31.\nMiG-31.\nSecond on the list is the MiG-31 fighter, which remains a promising aircraft despite its age, an air battle plane, the great power of weapons and the ability to launch hypersonic missiles, including into space.\nJ-16\nThe J-16 is a Chinese ghost-developed model of the Su-35, as a legend of the Soviet aircraft industry.\nSu-35\nSu-35\nIt is also a Russian upgraded version of the Su-35 equipped with modern radars and a target detection station.\nIts projected introduction of the powerful R-37 and Ka-77 missiles will expand the aircraft \u2019 s capabilities and increase its export capability.\nJ-10\nThe J-10 is a Chinese 4 + + generation light fighter equipped with modern electronic warfare equipment and a wide range of missiles.\nIn addition, it is less expensive to produce and maintain than the J-16.\nSource: Rossiyskaya Gazeta\nAgree.\nThis website uses cookies. You can read the terms of use to activate this feature by clicking here","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2022-0014.json.gz:44901","uncompressed_offset":1008363996,"url":"arabic.rt.com/technology/1354687-%D8%B5%D8%AD%D9%8A%D9%81%D8%A9-%D8%A3%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%83%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%AC-%D8%B3%D9%88-35-%D9%88%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%BA-31-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%B7%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AE%D9%85%D8%B3/","warc_date":"2022-05-17T15:09:20.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:82c7d54c-fbec-441a-91f2-7aca1b82742c>","warc