cadres.\nIt also set standards in attracting government leaders on a scientific and global basis through the houses of expertise and global advisory teams in attracting government leaders for leadership and innovation.\nEarly efforts were initiated in the Kingdom through the establishment of the Performance Measurement Center for Governmental Organizations, which measures the performance of public agencies with international standards, towards outstanding government performance, and a national vision achieved.\nHe introduced programs aimed at developing the skills of business leaders and IT managers in government agencies to achieve the vision and values of digital government, where the program consists of several development programs in the latest digital topics, which are offered in partnership with the top 100 international universities to identify the best global technical practices.\nThe programs continued to be rolled out through the 10X Saudi Leadership Program, which builds key leadership skills based on the 2030 Leaders Competencies Framework. The program aims to:\n1.\nBuilding successful leaders.\n2.\nEmpower leaders to strategize, innovate, and make impact.\n3.\nDeveloping competencies in order to achieve Vision 2030.\nThere are great programs in the development of organizations and strategic leaders in government organizations, which prompted me to search for the reasons of excellence of organizations in developed countries, and I found that the main supporter in the industry of leadership and innovation through professional leaders that achieve government excellence, leadership and innovation.\nBy reviewing the table of weights of the relative importance of the seven main criteria of European excellence 2020 are:\nAxis of Direction:\n\u2022 Goal and strategic vision were given a score of 100\n\u2022 Organizational culture and leadership were given a score of 100\nIn the implementation of Exception:\nThe employee engagement standard was given a score of 