sional competencies represented by 120 degrees\nThe third criterion: Attributes and relations 20% and a score of 200 out of the total scores of criteria 1000 degrees and is divided into:\nProfessional traits and self-growth are represented by 70 degrees\nRelations and social responsibility represented by 70 degrees\n3. Communication, communication and community service represented by 60 degrees\nThrough the use of this model to attract strategic leadership competencies, many countries have recorded successive successes and progress in their ranking of developed countries or the top 20 countries.\nThe Kingdom has recorded the best international practices in the number of training hours for government leadership cadres, and we appreciate these efforts through the keenness of the governors in devoting efforts and continuous support to the development of government organizations that promote the future of our great country.\nThese efforts have been reflected in the achievements of our dear Great Kingdom at all levels, including:\n\u2022 Sports Stations in 2021\n\u2022 Hosting Dacre Rally Saudi Arabia\n\u2022 Holding the second edition of the (Saudi Cup) horse race\n\u2022 Hosting the seventh season of the ABB FIA Formula E World Championship at the historic Diriyah Circuit\n\u2022 Hosting the electric car race (Xtreme E) in the historical province of Al-Ula\n\u2022 Hosting the 14th edition of the World Club Handball Championship (Superglobe) in Jeddah\n\u2022 Hosting a Formula 1 race\n\u2022 Cultural Stations in 2021\n\u2022 Launch of Noor Riyadh Exhibition\n\u2022 Honoring the winners of the National Cultural Awards Initiative\n\u2022 Inscription of the Cultural District (Fever) on the UNESCO World Heritage List\n\u2022 Riyadh International Book Fair\n\u2022 Binalsoor Exhibition in Riyadh\n\u2022 Hosted the Tuwaiq International Sculpture Symposium\n\u2022 Exhibition at Binalsoor in Jeddah\n\u2022 The first edition of the Red Sea International Film Festival\n\u2022 Launching (Diriyah Biennial) as the first Biennial held in the Kingdom\n\u2022 Launch of the strategy of the Bin Salman International Center for Arabic Calligraphy\nFinancial sustainability\nThe Kingdom of Saudi Arabia \u2019 s efforts in financial sustainability have resulted in the return of the economy to pre-pandemic levels in 2021. The total real results achieved a positive growth of 3.2% in 2021 compared to last year, while non-oil activities achieved a positive growth of 6.1% in 2021 compared to last year.\nDiversified economy\nLocal content\nAs a result of the initiative of localization and transfer of oil and gas technology and the increase of the share of local content in the oil and gas sector by 60%, in the context of empowering small, medium and finite enterprises, the year 2021 saw a number of possibilities provided to them to achieve the goal of vision of the contribution of small and medium enterprises total local results to 35% in 2030.\nThe rate of foreign direct investment in the second quarter of 2021 recorded the highest quarterly value during 2020, the previous years by about 13.8 billion dollars, recording an increase of 607.3, on a quarterly basis and an increase of 1573.9, on an annual basis.\nIn the tourism sector\nIn 2021, the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia will attract 10 million visitors from inside and outside the Kingdom by the vision 2030 that tourism will generate revenues of 50 billion Saudi riyals through diversified investments.\nof entrepreneurial projects\nThe NEOM project in total targets 380,000 jobs and contribute to the national domestic production 180 billion riyals by 2030.\nThe Red Sea Project\nOne of the mega projects in the vision of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia in 2030, which was designed by the project (Coral Bloom) with new beaches more than 90 islands will be placed in this project, the island will include resorts and operational hotels, a number of famous international hospitality pioneers, also in the resort (Dok butchers) Th