{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T146","run_id":"dog","topic_id":"1016","task":"multilingual","request_id":"1016","narrative_id":"1016"},"responses":[{"citations":{"4a564c34-5ed1-4d7d-961c-125e44d9f0aa_999086473":1.0},"text":"The contemporary Internet-era flat Earth believers are a group of individuals who, despite overwhelming scientific evidence, believe that the Earth is flat, rather than an oblate spheroid shape."},{"citations":{"4a564c34-5ed1-4d7d-961c-125e44d9f0aa_999086473":1.0},"text":"This notion has been around for centuries, but the modern flat Earth movement has gained significant traction online, with various organizations and public figures promoting this idea."},{"citations":{"4a564c34-5ed1-4d7d-961c-125e44d9f0aa_999086473":1.0},"text":"One of the key factors contributing to the resurgence of flat Earth beliefs is the widespread use of social media platforms, which have enabled the rapid dissemination of misinformation and conspiracy theories."},{"citations":{"23b3f452-0d7f-49b9-898d-fa51ce1e5529_717482675":1.0},"text":"According to a study by the University of New Hampshire, millennials and supporters of ex-president Trump are more likely to be open to conspiracy theories, including the flat Earth idea."},{"citations":{"23b3f452-0d7f-49b9-898d-fa51ce1e5529_717482675":1.0},"text":"The study found that acceptance or openness to conspiracy beliefs was significantly higher among these subgroups, with 22% of millennials and 25% of Trump supporters believing that the Earth is flat."},{"citations":{"f61994b0-dc34-40d6-a1e2-a7f66b22774b_548175167":1.0},"text":"The flat Earth movement has also been fueled by the rise of conspiracy theories, which have been imported into the Arab world and other parts of the globe."},{"citations":{"f61994b0-dc34-40d6-a1e2-a7f66b22774b_548175167":1.0},"text":"In the United States, the flat Earth movement has been promoted by individuals such as John Jasper, who preached about the idea in the southern states, and William Carpenter, who supported the theory and distributed thousands of copies of flat Earth books."},{"citations":{"4a564c34-5ed1-4d7d-961c-125e44d9f0aa_999086473":1.0},"text":"The arguments used by flat-earthers to prove their point of view are often based on misinterpretations of scientific data and a lack of understanding of astronomical phenomena."},{"citations":{"4a564c34-5ed1-4d7d-961c-125e44d9f0aa_999086473":1.0},"text":"For example, some flat-earthers claim that the Earth looks flat when viewed from a distance, or that the lack of visible curvature is evidence that the Earth is not round."},{"citations":{"4a564c34-5ed1-4d7d-961c-125e44d9f0aa_999086473":1.0},"text":"However, these claims are easily debunked by scientific evidence, including satellite imagery and spacecraft observations, which clearly show the Earth to be an oblate spheroid shape."},{"citations":{"23b3f452-0d7f-49b9-898d-fa51ce1e5529_717482675":1.0},"text":"Despite the overwhelming evidence against it, the flat Earth movement continues to attract new followers, who are often drawn in by online videos and social media posts promoting the idea."},{"citations":{"23b3f452-0d7f-49b9-898d-fa51ce1e5529_717482675":1.0},"text":"The role of social media in spreading conspiracy theories, including the flat Earth idea, is a significant factor in the resurgence of this notion."},{"citations":{"23b3f452-0d7f-49b9-898d-fa51ce1e5529_717482675":1.0},"text":"As one expert noted, social media platforms like YouTube can create a \"rabbit hole\" effect, where users are recommended videos that promote conspiracy theories, making it seem like the whole world is talking about the flat Earth."},{"citations":{"4a564c34-5ed1-4d7d-961c-125e44d9f0aa_999086473":1.0},"text":"In conclusion, the contemporary Internet-era flat Earth believers are a group of individuals who, despite overwhelming scientific evidence, believe that the Earth is flat, rather than an oblate spheroid shape."},{"citations":{"4a564c34-5ed1-4d7d-961c-125e44d9f0aa_999086473":1.0},"text":"The movement has been fueled by the rise of conspiracy theories, social media, and the promotion of the idea by various organizations and public figures."},{"citations":{"23b3f452-0d7f-49b9-898d-fa51ce1e5529_717482675":1.0},"text":"The characteristics of people who are most likely to subscribe to flat Earth beliefs include millennials and supporters of ex-president Trump, who are more open to conspiracy theories."},{"citations":{"23b3f452-0d7f-49b9-898d-fa51ce1e5529_717482675":1.0},"text":"Overall, the flat Earth movement is a complex phenomenon that highlights the need for critical thinking and media literacy in the digital age."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"4a564c34-5ed1-4d7d-961c-125e44d9f0aa_999086473":1.0},"text":"The contemporary Internet-era flat Earth believers are a group of individuals who, despite overwhelming scientific evidence, believe that the Earth is flat, rather than an oblate spheroid shape."},{"citations":{"4a564c34-5ed1-4d7d-961c-125e44d9f0aa_999086473":1.0},"text":"This notion has been around for centuries, but the modern flat Earth movement has gained significant traction online, with various organizations and public figures promoting this idea."},{"citations":{"4a564c34-5ed1-4d7d-961c-125e44d9f0aa_999086473":1.0},"text":"One of the key factors contributing to the resurgence of flat Earth beliefs is the widespread use of social media platforms, which have enabled the rapid dissemination of misinformation and conspiracy theories."},{"citations":{"23b3f452-0d7f-49b9-898d-fa51ce1e5529_717482675":1.0},"text":"According to a study by the University of New Hampshire, millennials and supporters of ex-president Trump are more likely to be open to conspiracy theories, including the flat Earth idea."},{"citations":{"23b3f452-0d7f-49b9-898d-fa51ce1e5529_717482675":1.0},"text":"The study found that acceptance or openness to conspiracy beliefs was significantly higher among these subgroups, with 22% of millennials and 25% of Tr