traction\" of the work, \"the concept\" should be placed on the secondary, bluntly, \"they should revise the line\", and added that \"it is not necessary to completely put the concept into, but until then, the most important thing is to create the audience. It's a role that captures the eyes of the audience.\"\n[Advertisement] Please continue reading...\nThe director of the animated version of \"Little Mermaid\" believes that the live-action version should be more about the relationship between father and daughter.\n(Courtesy of Disney)\nJohn Musk emphasized that Disney \u2019 s classics were never born out of preconceived ideas, but rather immersed the audience in the world built by the story and the characters.\nHe believes that while it is not necessary to completely abandon the concept, before that, you should first create characters that the audience can feel and feel attracted to.\nAs for Disney \u2019 s frequent remakes of old animations into live-action versions, he believes that this is to make the audience like things, and then sell them again, and he obviously does not agree with this practice.\nDisney \u2019 s remake of the classic animation, apart from Aladdin, has a mostly bad reputation. John Musk pointed to the 2023 live-action version of \u201cThe Little Mermaid \u201d and bluntly said:\u201c They don \u2019 t put much ink on the story of their father and daughter, that \u2019 s the core of the whole movie. \u201d The lions in the Lion King are much richer.\nShare with friends:\n\u203b This article is copyrighted and cannot be reproduced without permission. [ETtoday Copyright Notice] \u203b","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2024-0014.json.gz:10299","uncompressed_offset":1002818262,"url":"star.ettoday.net/news/2747893","warc_date":"2024-05-28T23:34:55.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:9bf4d61e-80c6-417e-8c40-6d987236d4fb>","warc_url":"https://star.ettoday.net/news/2747893"},"created":"2024-05-29T01:09:01.000Z","lang":"eng"}