lso accounted for a considerable amount of space, the additional edition of \"Detective Story\" added \"Little Roosevelt's\" First Lady Detective Case \",\" The Cat Detective Case \"female writer Lilian Brown\", style change New materials were added to the four articles of Keigo Higashino and the New Trend of Reasoning Novels and the Past and Present of Chinese Detective Reasoning Novels.\nAged yellow flowers\nIn his later years, Du left behind two books, one is a memoir, \"Years of Yellow Flowers: The Search of Three Generations\", and the other is a collection of essays, \"Long Face Memories: The Eyes of Teachers and Friends.\"\nFrom the childhood of the beacon fire (1935 \u2013 1946), experienced the ideal pursuit of studying in mainland China, the anti-rightist struggle, and the storm of the Cultural Revolution. After 20 years in mainland China, he returned to Hong Kong and lived in Hong Kong for another 20 years.\nDue to the serious illness of his mother, Tu Chin returned to Hong Kong with the President of the Xinhua News Agency, Mr Leung Wai-lin, and then came to Hong Kong with a one-way permit to accompany his father, Dr Li Song, to work in a pharmacy.\nIn the past 20 years in mainland China, many books can not be seen, so once in Hong Kong, they constantly buy books to read.\nDu Jian bought a collection of poems by Kahlil Gibran and translated some of the novels, but he wanted to kill time and practice writing. Moreover, \"In the past few years, the pollution caused by the language of the Cultural Revolution in China, when I opened the newspaper, I saw all the big stories and false stories and official words, and it was best to clean the scum of my own language and words. I was able to learn his writing skills and practice my own Chinese writing, so I started translating Gibberlain \u2019 s novels. \u201d\nHe does not want to hide in the willow.\nDu Jian went to the \"New Evening News\" to see the work, Rover asked Du Jian to translate a draft to see, Du Jian reluctantly to his own translation of the novel and the introduction of Ji Boren's short article to Rover.\nThe next day, Du Jian opened the \"New Evening News\" and found that his article introducing Gilbert was published in the newspaper.\nAs a result, Du turned to work at the newspaper office, because the newspaper was short of people, so he worked in the supplement of the newspaper.\nHe changed his name to Dujuan, meaning Dujuan Dujuan, to \"Dujuan Dujuan\".\nMy handwritten collection of Kiberon's novels, a small book by Daguang Publishing House in 1975, is a collection of translations from Du Jian's that year.\nDu Jian said in \"The Golden Flower of Time\" that Zhang Huai, editor of Daguang Publishing House, is his acquaintance and has published several books for him, including \"Life and Death\", \"People at the bottom\", \"New District Governor\", \"Golden City of Blood\", etc. These books are not easy to find nowadays.\nTeacher 's Eyes\nIn the preface to the book \"I Know Du Zhen\", the subtitle of \"The Yellow Flower of Time\", Lan Zhen points out that \"The Yellow Flower of Time\" \"tells the story of the three generations of his family (grandfather Pan Ta Wei, father Li Song and Li Wenjian) who followed the truth and participated in the democratic revolution.\" His father was a little older, and his father was a little older, and his father was a little older, and he was a little older, and he was a little older.\nIt is divided into two parts: the first part is \"Teacher's Letters\", which, as the name suggests, are reminiscent of teachers and friends, including Lun, Chen Ti, Wu Chi-min, Lu Fu, Yen Ching-shu, Fan Yong, An Tzu Chieh, Kang Chun-fang, Li Liang-min, Xiao Qian Qian, Xu Xu, Lin Nien-tong, Huang Kuo-chih, Ma Kuo-chuan, and Qian. In the second half of the book, \"Looking Back on History,\" Du Chien writes about the old stories of Liao An-hsiang, Pan Chu, Huang Leng-kuan, Pan Ta-wei, and Chen Lu-kui.\nThere are a number of overlaps between the \"Love of the Teacher\" and the \"Yellow Flower of the Year\". \"From scratch\" is a macroscopic view, and \"Love of the Teacher\" is even a micro-close-up. Du Jian writes old prose with the pen of a novelist. It is better to be lively and friendly, and everyone is alive. \u2014 Remembering my grandfather, Pan Ta-wei \u201d is a particularly detailed and wonderful article. Pan Ta-wei was influenced by Sun Yat-sen \u2019 s ideas and joined the Xingzhong Society. Later, Pan Ta-wei became the organizer of the Southern Section of the League.\nThe most famous story of Pan Ta-wei is the collection of the remains of the 72 martyrs of Huang Hua-gang. This passage is told by Du Chien through the words of his mother-in-law, Chen Wei-chang. When Chen Wei-chang died, Du Chien was very young. It was impossible to record his mother-in-law \u2019 s words. In other words, Du Chien used a small pen. The story of his father is told in the book of Revelation, and the story of his father is told in the book of Revelation.\nAuthor: Wu Chi-min, editor of Readers \u2019 Liangyou Monthly (1984-1988, 45 issues), Science and Science Fiction Series (1990, 4 volumes) and Readers \u2019 Liangyou Library (10 volumes), Zhao Jiabi, Liang Yusheng, Hsu Ting-ming, Dong Ding-shan, Hsiao Chien, Ku Tsang-wu, Huang Ji-shih, Chen Hui-yang and Du Chien-chun.\nCombining \"The Yellow Flower of the Year\" and \"The Memory of the Long Face\", now imagining Du Jian's career of writing books, translating books, and compiling books is bound to feel wonderful.\nby Vincent Cheng\nArt \u2022 Liu Ruoji\nEditors \u2022 Chu Chien-hsun\nEmail \u2022 literature @ mingpao.com\nfb: http: / / www.facebook.com / SundayMingpao\nPrevious / Next News","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2022-0025.json.gz:20726","uncompressed_offset":38674691,"url":"news.mingpao.com/pns/%E5%89%AF%E5%88%8A/article/20220828/s00005/1661622390273/%E6%98%9F%E6%9C%9F%E6%97%A5%E6%96%87%E5%AD%B8-%E6%9D%9C%E6%BC%B8-%E6%AD%B2%E6%9C