cology of the green wall.\nAccording to the Environmental Protection Bureau of Chiayi City Government, since 2019, the Environmental Protection Department has promoted the vertical air green wall project. Since 2019, three schools, including Xingjia, Jiabei Elementary School and Jiabei Elementary School, have installed climbing plants on the school's daughter wall and the balcony of the classroom.\nThe Environmental Protection Bureau of the Chiayi Municipal Government said that this year, the Environmental Protection Agency expanded the target of subsidies, in addition to the original subsidies of public middle school, public elementary school, public preschool institutions, public welfare groups, public facilities, environmental protection night market, civic activity center and other venues, air green wall subsidies of 3,000 to 6,000 yuan per square meter, single subsidy ceiling of 400,000 yuan.\nAccording to the Municipal Environmental Protection Agency, according to the results of the study, vertical green walls can reduce the concentration of nitrogen dioxide (NO2), suspended particulates (PM10) by about 40% and 60%, but also reduce the concentration of indoor fine suspended particulates (PM2.5) by about 10%, ozone by about 30%, and indoor temperature reduction by about 1.8 \u2103.\nAccording to the city's Environmental Protection Bureau, the appropriate plant types are lily bamboo, firecracker red, Yunnan yellow carnation, turtle, Boston kidney fern, hydrangea, African pansy or panthera, and can be selected according to the space planning and installation requirements, so that the space is more beautiful.\n# Green Wall # Cooling # EPB # EPD # Planting","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2022-0000.json.gz:11290","uncompressed_offset":535735985,"url":"www.chinatimes.com/realtimenews/20220104004832-260405","warc_date":"2022-01-04T11:35:35.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:70b30305-e209-49f4-aa22-78908d3f1880>","warc_url":"https://www.chinatimes.com/realtimenews/20220104004832-260405"},"created":"2022-01-04T12:10:00.000Z","lang":"eng"},"9c1da28b-f3a2-4627-ac08-62956eeeeade_668324008":{"id":"9c1da28b-f3a2-4627-ac08-62956eeeeade_668324008","text":"Make your home more stylish!\n6 wonderful examples of ornamental plants\nGenie Chien\nLoading admin actions \u2026\nDo you like gardening? If you like flowers and plants, you can use ornamental plants as materials for interior decoration! Green has a natural beauty and charm, and it is easy to match with furniture and space, which is an indispensable element of interior decoration.\nWith them, even if it is not a beautiful house, it can make your home look radiant with fresh green.\nLet \u2019 s take a look at the 6 ideas that make a stylish home out of plants!\nExample 1: The Little Forest in the House\nDo you want to live in a forest?\nThe designer saw through your mind and specially redesigned this house into a forest landscape.\nThis home is made of light wood and white, where green plants grow everywhere, creating a beautiful visual feel.\nLiving here, you can feel the natural atmosphere in all seasons, and your body and mind will feel extremely relaxed and comfortable!\nExample 2: Bold use of plants to decorate home space\nThis open space combines a living room, dining room and kitchen, where designers use plants to make bold d\u00e9cor.\nThe rows of trees grow against the wall to form a beautiful vision. The indoor movement line is unparalleled, and living here is not only extremely relieving, but also can breathe the green verdant at the same time!\nExample 3: Green interior wall\nThe interior is decorated with a vertically-green botanical garden, from the ceiling to the floor. Not only is it impressive at first glance, but the three-dimensional shape is even more impressive! Facing these greenery every day is the most healing secret of the busy world!\nExample 4: A relaxing bathroom with a vacation style\nBathrooms with high humidity are also good for growing plants.\nHere, the designer uses white and green to make your bathroom a vacation retreat.\nIvy and ferns are ideal choices, and the space forms a balanced color, so beautiful that people do not want to leave!\nExample 5: Small green garden on the shelf\nIt is also a good idea to combine small ornamental plants with small accessories.\nThis way, using a rustic vine basket and small utensils, with beautiful green plants, creates a mini botanical garden in the space.\nIt not only makes the space more efficient, but also adds a lot of fun to life.\nExample 6: Smart use of the outdoor garden\nThis residence has green plants planted on the outdoor balcony, allowing their verdant greenery to penetrate the interior.\nSitting in the living room, you can observe the growth of plants through a large area of glass windows.\nIn order to make the whole picture look beautiful as a painting, the designer took special care to choose the right plant to make the perfect match, so that the visual beauty is more divided!\nIf you are looking for inspiration to decorate your home, you must not miss the following articles:\n12 Lighting Designs to Light Up the Appearance of Your Home!\nDo you need someone to help you design or build your home?\nFind a professional now!\nFind out more about home design!","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2022-0016.json.gz:31560","uncompressed_offset":668324008,"url":"www.homify.tw/ideabooks/1982859/%E8%AE%93%E5%AE%B6%E4%B8%AD%E6%9B%B4%E6%99%82%E5%B0%9A!-6-%E5%80%8B%E8%A7%80%E8%B3%9E%E7%94%A8%E6%A4%8D%E7%89%A9%E7%9A%84%E5%A6%99%E7%94%A8%E5%AF%A6%E4%BE%8B","warc_date":"2022-06-05T19:00:15.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:9c1da28b-f3a2-4627-ac08-62956eeeeade>","warc_url":"https://www.homify.tw/ideabooks/1982859/%E8%AE%93%E5%AE%B6%E4%B8%AD%E6%9B%B4%E6%99%82%E5%B0%9A!-6-%E5%80%8B%E8%A7%80%E8%B3%9E%E7%94%A8%E6%A4%8D%E7%89%A9%E7%9A%84%E5%A6%99%E7%94%A8%E5%AF%A6%E4%BE%8B"},"created":"2022-06-05T19:47:11.000Z","lang":"eng"},"1fb1e736-0025-4b5a-a95f-dd24f13370c7_147328356":{"id":"1fb1e736-0025-4b5a-a95f-dd24f13370c7_147328356","text":"Prince\u2019s Landscape Pte Ltd Now Provides Singapore Properties with Vertical Green Walls\n\nPrince\u2019s Landscape Pte Ltd is famous for its\u00a0vertical wall planters,\u00a0green walls and\u00a0flower backdrop in Singapore. The company caters to residential and commercial clients as well.\u00a0\n\nSingapore, 2023-Jan-04 \u2014 /EPR Network/ \u2014 Prince\u2019s Landscape Pte Ltd, the leading landscaping company in Singapore is offering vertical green walls to commercial and residential properties. Whether it is a retail showroom or a high rise, the vertical green wall is an innovative approach towards introducing nature amidst the concrete jungle.\n\nThe company uses quality\u00a0vertical wall planters, ensuring the healthy growth of the plants. These vertical walls are easy to maintain, assemble, install, disassemble, and reinstall. The technique used by Prince\u2019s Landscape Pte Ltd ensures the user does not have to spend much time tending and taking care of the plants.\n\nAlong with green walls, the company also provides clients with exquisite\u00a0flower backdrops in Singapore\u00a0to complement the greenery around them. It\u2019s a long-term investment as a green wall can last up to 25 years.\n\nVertical walls by Prince\u2019s Landscape Pte Ltd come with some unique features:\n\n  \u2022 Custom design to suit the client\u2019s needs.\n  \u2022 Minimal watering of the green wall plants.\n  \u2022 Ultra-low maintenance ensured.\n  \u2022 Quick installation due to a modular system.\n  \u2022 Use of plants that can survive in a tropical climate.\n\nWhy choose a vertical green wall?\n\n  \u2022 Reduces waste of energy.\n  \u2022 Improves air quality.\n  \u2022 Makes the structure sustainable.\n  \u2022 The space becomes more fire-resistant.\n  \u2022 Minimizes ambient noise.\n\nThe general installation cost for a vertical green wall by Prince\u2019s Landscape Pte Ltd ranges between $200 per square meter and $1200 per square meter, depending on the design, the kind of plants used and the installation process.\n\n\u00a0\n\nAbout the company:\n\nOne of the oldest nurseries in Singapore, Prince\u2019s Landscape Pte Ltd has 50 years of experience in the industry. Started out humbly as a flower shop, Prince\u2019s Landscape Pte Ltd have evolved into a full-fledged landscape design and installation specialist.\n\n\u00a0\n\nContact Details\n\nTelephone:\u00a065 6763 7000\n\nFax:\u00a065 6892 2700\n\nWhatsApp:\u00a0+65 8838 3479\n\nEmail:\u00a0buzz@prince.com.sg\n\nAddress:\u00a053 Sungei Tengah Road, Singapore 698998\n\nMatched content\n\nEditor\u2019s pick\n\nExpress Press Release Distribution","url":"https://express-press-release.net/news/2023/01/04/1319783"},"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749":{"id":"a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1_458215749","text":"In order to improve the environmental air quality and let children learn with peace of mind, the Taichung Municipal Environmental Protection Bureau has continued to build a clean air green wall in the school. This year, 12 schools in Jianping Elementary School, Juren Elementary School and Chongde Elementary School have received subsidies from the Environmental Protection Department.\nAccording to the Environmental Protection Bureau, through the installation of clean air green walls, indoor air quality can be improved. At present, space such as classroom corridors and flower stands outside the daughter wall in Taichung City can be planted, which can achieve the benefits of dust retention, air pollution absorption and temperature regulation.\nIn order to strengthen the protection of the school environment for children, the Taichung City Environmental Protection Bureau expanded the subsidy for the construction of a clean air green wall on the campus, and the current subsidy amount to 1.76 million yuan, with an area of 358 square meters.\nThe Environmental Protection Bureau stressed that currently selected plants that can purify the air and do not need to spend too much money and time to maintain include the Dragon Tubeh, the Junzi and Wu Bamboo, the Turtle, the Cannonflower or the Honeysuckle.\nHow good is the effect of clean air green wall?\nAccording to international research, vertical clean air green walls can reduce the concentration of nitrogen dioxide (NO2) and particulate matter (PM10) by about 40% and 60%. In addition, green walls can also reduce the concentration of fine particulate matter (PM2.5) in classrooms by about 10% and the concentration of ozone (O3) by about 30%.\nGreen wall is the most natural and energy efficient air purification facilities, no need to plug in electricity, self-circulation, to achieve the purpose of air purification, can be called the \"most environmentally friendly air purifier\".\nChen Hongyi, director of the Environmental Protection Bureau, said that in addition to blocking outdoor pollutants and improving indoor air, the air green wall can also adjust the temperature and drive energy conservation and carbon reduction. Next year, Taichung City is expected to expand the subsidy target, including community activity centers, public kindergartens and environmental night markets.\n# Green Wall # Air # Cleanliness # Campus # Environment","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2021-0034.json.gz:14270","uncompressed_offset":458215749,"url":"www.chinatimes.com/realtimenews/20211125003391-260405","warc_date":"2021-11-25T05:58:05.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:a89e20ea-c2ae-4600-8704-7d23939dacc1>","warc_url":"https://www.chinatimes.com/realtimenews/20211125003391-260405"},"created":"2021-11-25T06:35:23.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
