s expected to grow by 13.43% annually from 2023 to 2028."},{"citations":{"292e2ff7-2382-4c0b-90aa-eb33e197caeb_265707900":1.0},"text":"Key national projects, such as the Benban solar park and the Gulf of Suez wind project in Egypt, are among the largest renewable energy projects in the Middle East."},{"citations":{"292e2ff7-2382-4c0b-90aa-eb33e197caeb_265707900":1.0},"text":"These efforts are expected to have a positive impact on both the local economy and climate goals, with the region positioning itself as a leader in the renewable energy sector."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"b273dfa1-1337-44eb-9c37-24aa1b0ea1d0_1026721432":1.0},"text":"The Middle East, traditionally known for its oil wealth, is undergoing a significant energy transition, with several countries investing heavily in solar energy."},{"citations":{"b273dfa1-1337-44eb-9c37-24aa1b0ea1d0_1026721432":1.0},"text":"Countries such as the UAE, Saudi Arabia, Jordan, Oman, and Egypt are boosting investment in the clean energy sector, with the UAE investing Dh600 billion ($163.5bn) in clean and renewable energy projects over the next three decades."},{"citations":{"b273dfa1-1337-44eb-9c37-24aa1b0ea1d0_1026721432":1.0},"text":"The UAE aims to achieve net zero emissions by 2050 and is building the world's largest solar plant with a capacity of two gigawatts in Abu Dhabi's Al Dhafra region."},{"citations":{"b273dfa1-1337-44eb-9c37-24aa1b0ea1d0_1026721432":1.0},"text":"Saudi Arabia, the Arab world's largest economy, has also announced new renewable energy projects as it seeks to become carbon neutral by 2060."},{"citations":{"06ba619d-aab0-4d8e-9624-e4ac111589d1_480105281":1.0},"text":"The Middle East and North Africa region has one of the highest levels of solar energy potential in the world, with countries such as Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates, Morocco, and Egypt contributing on average annual solar radiation exceeding 2,000 kilowatt-hours per square meter per year."},{"citations":{"06ba619d-aab0-4d8e-9624