macists released a survey that found that most non-chain pharmacies are struggling to fill employee vacancies and cope with supply chain disruptions."},{"citations":{"3cb6d465-6538-4ce4-9d4f-649316109ee8_980828607":1.0},"text":"Sixty percent of pharmacies surveyed said they were dealing with supply chain disruptions, and nearly 70 percent said it was difficult to fill staff vacancies."},{"citations":{"2b594cc2-e41f-46db-a26c-7a42ec0c6695_921023273":1.0},"text":"A global study by The Lancet found that there are about 6.4 million doctors missing in the world, and globally, there are more than 43 million health workers missing when comparing the current level of coverage with the targets needed to achieve universal health coverage."},{"citations":{"2b594cc2-e41f-46db-a26c-7a42ec0c6695_921023273":1.0},"text":"The study, titled \u201cMeasuring human resource affordability for health and its relationship to universal health coverage for 204 countries and territories from 1990 to 2019: a systematic analysis for the Global Burden of Disease Study,\u201d was published May 23 in The Lancet."},{"citations":{"2b594cc2-e41f-46db-a26c-7a42ec0c6695_921023273":1.0},"text":"The authors studied the number of doctors, nurses, and midwives, dental and pharmaceutical staff and found that as of 2019, there were shortages of doctors in 132 countries."},{"citations":{"d940eba4-d6df-4958-a023-bfd57f6a9042_207602049":1.0},"text":"The healthcare systems are coping with the shortages by delaying, canceling, or rationing care, switching to alternate drugs, and finding or substituting drugs and changing treatment plans as needed."},{"citations":{"5ce83679-158d-4b58-b20f-9f406ab7e58b_193716476":1.0},"text":"The American Society of Health-System Pharmacists CEO, Paul Abramowitz, said that almost all categories of drugs are facing shortages, and the organization is working to monitor the supply chain and take measures to address the shortages."},{"citations":{"3cb6d465-6538-4ce4-9d4f-649316109ee8_980828607":1.0},"text":"The FDA is also working to monitor the supply chain and take measures to address the shortages, with the agency pointing out that it will continue to take measures to monitor the supply chain."},{"citations":{"039b72ee-9139-416e-9f1b-92b866fc03b0_1066817968":1.0},"text":"In conclusion, the medication shortage is a growing global concern, impacting both developing and developed countries, with reports of shortages of medications and/or medical supplies in hospitals and pharmacies increasing between 2021 and 2024."},{"citations":{"d940eba4-d6df-4958-a023-bfd57f6a9042_207602049":1.0},"text":"The shortage of drugs is affecting a wide range of medications, including cancer chemotherapy drugs, emergency drugs, and common antibiotics, and is prompting hospitals to find or substitute drugs and change treatment plans as needed."},{"citations":{"d940eba4-d6df-4958-a023-bfd57f6a9042_207602049":1.0},"text":"The healthcare systems are coping with the shortages by delaying, canceling, or rationing care, switching to alternate drugs, and finding or substituting drugs and changing treatment plans as needed."},{"citations":{"5ce83679-158d-4b58-b20f-9f406ab7e58b_193716476":1.0},"text":"The American Society of Health-System Pharmacists and the FDA are working to monitor the supply chain and take measures to address the shortages."},{"citations":{"2b594cc2-e41f-46db-a26c-7a42ec0c6695_921023273":1.0},"text":"The global study by The Lancet found that there are about 6.4 million doctors missing in the world, and globally, there are more than 43 million health workers missing when comparing the current level of coverage with the targets needed to achieve universal health coverage."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"3cb6d465-6538-4ce4-9d4f-649316109ee8_980828607":1.0},"text":"The medication shortage is a growing global concern, impacting both developing and developed countries, with reports of shortages of medications and/or medical supplies in hospitals and pharmacies incre