{"d940eba4-d6df-4958-a023-bfd57f6a9042_207602049":1.0},"text":"In some cases, there are no alternatives to the affected drugs, which puts patients at risk, according to Paul Abramowitz, CEO of the American Society of Health-System Pharmacists."},{"citations":{"039b72ee-9139-416e-9f1b-92b866fc03b0_1066817968":1.0},"text":"The five categories of drugs with the greatest deficiency include central nervous system stimulants, antimicrobials, hormonal agents, and intravenous fluids, in addition to the 32 chemotherapy drugs that are deficient."},{"citations":{"039b72ee-9139-416e-9f1b-92b866fc03b0_1066817968":1.0},"text":"The Drug Deficiency Database maintained by the American Society of Health System Pharmacists and the University of Utah is based on voluntary reports from practitioners, patients, and others that have been confirmed by manufacturers."},{"citations":{"039b72ee-9139-416e-9f1b-92b866fc03b0_1066817968":1.0},"text":"The crisis has lasted for a year and a half, with more than half of the treatment shortages lasting for more than two years, according to an analysis by health consultancy IQVIA."},{"citations":{"039b72ee-9139-416e-9f1b-92b866fc03b0_1066817968":1.0},"text":"The average shortage affects at least half a million patients, many of them elderly, according to the US."},{"citations":{"3cb6d465-6538-4ce4-9d4f-649316109ee8_980828607":1.0},"text":"The FDA pointed out that about 111 drugs are out of stock in the United States, including the heart disease drug digoxin injection, the chemical drug Dacarbazine, and some antibiotics."},{"citations":{"3cb6d465-6538-4ce4-9d4f-649316109ee8_980828607":1.0},"text":"The US supply chain crisis continues, with many goods facing shortages, and the Federal Reserve warned that large parts of the United States had begun to be affected by supply chain disruptions and labor shortages."},{"citations":{"3cb6d465-6538-4ce4-9d4f-649316109ee8_980828607":1.0},"text":"A survey by the National Association of Community Pharmacists found that most non-chain pharmacies are struggling to fill employee vacancies and cope with supply chain disruptions, with 60% of pharmacies surveyed saying they were dealing with supply chain disruptions."},{"citations":{"3cb6d465-6538-4ce4-9d4f-649316109ee8_980828607":1.0},"text":"Nearly 70% of pharmacies surveyed said it was difficult to fill staff vacancies, highlighting the challenges faced by healthcare systems in coping with medication shortages."},{"citations":{"5ce83679-158d-4b58-b20f-9f406ab7e58b_193716476":1.0},"text":"The widely used diabetes drugs Ozempic and Mounjaro, the allergy treatment drug adrenaline, the common antibiotic amoxicillin for children, chemotherapy drugs, and injections commonly used in hospitals in intensive care are among the drugs affected by the shortages."},{"citations":{"5ce83679-158d-4b58-b20f-9f406ab7e58b_193716476":1.0},"text":"The American Society of Health System Pharmacists and the Utah Center for Drug Information Services reported that a total of 323 drugs in the United States were in severe shortages in the first quarter of 2024."},{"citations":{"2b594cc2-e41f-46db-a26c-7a42ec0c6695_921023273":1.0},"text":"The medication shortage is not limited to the United States, with a global study by The Lancet finding that there are about 6.4 million doctors missing in the world, and more than 43 million health workers missing when comparing the current level of coverage with the targets needed to achieve universal health coverage."},{"citations":{"2b594cc2-e41f-46db-a26c-7a42ec0c6695_921023273":1.0},"text":"The study found that as of 2019, there were shortages of doctors in 132 countries, highlighting the need for adequate numbers of health workers to achieve universal health coverage."},{"citations":{"039b72ee-9139-416e-9f1b-92b866fc03b0_1066817968":1.0},"text":"In conclusion, the medication shortage is a growing global concern, with reports of shortages of medications and/or medical supplies in hospitals and pharmacies increasing between 2021 and 2024, affecting both developing and developed countries."},{"citations":{"d940eba4-d6df-4958-a023-bfd57f6a9042_207602049":1.0},"text":"The reasons behind the shortages are complex and multifaceted, including supply chain disruptions, labor shortages, and manufacturing delays, and healthcare systems are coping with the shortages by finding or substituting drugs, changing treatment plans, and rationing care."},{"citations":{"039b72ee-9139-416e-9f1b-92b866fc03b0_1066817968":1.0},"text":"However, the medication shortage remains a significant challenge, with many patients at risk due to the lack of access to essential medications, and urgent action is needed to address the shortage and ensure that all patients have access to the medications they need."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"3cb6d465-6538-4ce4-9d4f-649316109ee8_980828607":1.0},"text":"The medication shortage is a growing global concern, impacting both developing and developed countries, with reports of shortages of medications and/or medical supplies in hospitals and pharmacies increasing between 2021 and 2024."},{"citations":{"039b72ee-9139-416e-9f1b-92b866fc03b0_1066817968":1.0},"text":"According to the American Society of Health System Pharmacists and the University of Utah Drug Information Service, organizations began tracking drug shortages for the first time in 2001, and the deficit is now at a record level."},{"citations":{"039b72ee-9139-416e-9f1b-92b866fc03b0_1066817968":1.0},"text":"As of the first three months of 2024, there were 323 drugs in short supply in the United States, surpassing the record of 320 in 2014."},{"citations":{"039b72ee-9139-416e-9f1b-92b866fc03b0_1066817968":1.0},"text":"The CEO of the American Society of Health System Pharmacists, Paul Abramowitz, stated that all drug classes are vulnerable to shortages, with some of the most worrisome shortages including sterile injectable generic drugs, including cancer chemotherapy drugs and emergency drugs stored in hospital vans and 