ndustry."},{"citations":{"a90fed0f-41a3-49e4-85e1-ade7b9b5f6fa_334539654":1.0},"text":"The film \"Crowded Out: The Story of Overtourism\" explores the impacts of overtourism on local communities and the environment, featuring interviews with local residents and global experts."},{"citations":{"e8218fac-be75-450d-a3c6-ce96b2808e2e_476571446":1.0},"text":"Overall, the causes and consequences of overtourism are complex and multifaceted, requiring a nuanced and sustainable approach to tourism management that prioritizes the needs of local communities and the environment."},{"citations":{"a90fed0f-41a3-49e4-85e1-ade7b9b5f6fa_334539654":1.0},"text":"By understanding the social, environmental, and economic impacts of overtourism, we can work towards developing strategies that promote responsible and sustainable tourism practices, preserving the integrity of local communities and the environment for future generations."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"e8218fac-be75-450d-a3c6-ce96b2808e2e_476571446":1.0},"text":"The phenomenon of overtourism has become a significant concern in various parts of the world, affecting not only the environment but also the social and economic fabric of local communities."},{"citations":{"4bd649f2-da29-4279-8605-12dc0f8367d9_38011106":1.0},"text":"Overtourism occurs when the number of tourists exceeds the capacity of a destination, leading to a decline in the quality of life for local residents and causing environmental damage."},{"citations":{"e8218fac-be75-450d-a3c6-ce96b2808e2e_476571446":1.0},"text":"This phenomenon has been observed in popular tourist destinations such as Bangkok in Thailand, Paris in France, and New York in the United States, as well as in some Greek and Spanish cities."},{"citations":{"e8218fac-be75-450d-a3c6-ce96b2808e2e_476571446":1.0},"text":"The influx of tourists has led to overcrowding, making it difficult for locals to access basic services and amenities, and has also driven up the cost of living, making it expensive for 