add: \u201cWe provide a calm and safe atmosphere for our furry companions. Our puppies are free to roam around during the hour to play, sleep and enjoy the attention they receive from humans. Our classes are there to create playtime and socialisation before they go to their forever home.\n\nREAD MORE: RSPCA rescue Spaniel puppy 'dumped in a box with his dying brother' on Essex roadside\n\nREAD MORE:Pebbles the instantly recognisable 'campus cat' at the University of Essex who now has his own statue\n\n\u201cWe have the highest safety standards and you can enjoy our classes knowing that we only work with reputable breeders who have the highest standards of care, we also donate to rescue charities each month.\n\nClasses are for beginners aged 14 and over and aim to create a stress-free environment. A fully qualified yoga teacher will work with you through mainly floor postures, so you\u2019re on a level with the puppies and kittens. Cuddles are optional.\n\nTime spent with a fluffy companion has been proven to have a massive impact on mental health, with 37% of people saying that their pets help them with their lives, according to a Blue Cross study. Just being around animals can have a positive impact on our mental health.\n\nAt Pawz and Tails, their classes \u201cprovide a haven of pure uplifting bliss, interacting with baby animals is extremely heart warming and you will leave us with a big smile on your face. It's also a fun time for our furry companions, who love to play and be cuddled\u201d.\n\nThe animals brought in for the yoga classes are brought from responsible breeders who are looking to socialise the little ones, and Pawz and Tails donate to rescue charities every month.\n\nGet more news from EssexLive straight to your inbox for FREE","url":"https://www.essexlive.news/whats-on/whats-on-news/essex-yoga-venue-puppies-kittens-9328087"},"c9efec55-9a18-4405-8637-b047656c1cc8_254307737":{"id":"c9efec55-9a18-4405-8637-b047656c1cc8_254307737","text":"If you want to play fancy punch power, you can't do small aerial yoga fairies need to practice muscle.\nPost Date: November 02, 2021\nAerial yoga fever has swept Asia in the past two or three years, and many stars have been seen on social media wrapped around their bodies with silk cloths, hanging in the air like fairies to make a \"beautiful mirror\" stretching action, and fashionable ladies are also eager to try.\nBut these seemingly effortless movements, in fact, the difficulty is not small, must have a certain core muscle and upper limb strength to do, no expert guidance, should not be casually imitated!\nNew School Yoga Exercises All Body Muscles\nAerial yoga is the use of silk to create a suspended hammock (hammock) to support the body, or the silk wrapped around the body, to practice various yoga styles.\nAriel, a tutor with 3 years of experience in aerial yoga, pointed out that the traditional yoga done on the ground is also known as \u201cHatha Yoga \u201d and has a history of more than 1,000 years in India.\nAerial yoga has only begun to develop in the last 10 years and belongs to the new school of yoga.\nWhen it comes to yoga, the first thing that people think of may be the beautiful stretching exercises that improve body flexibility and posture.\nThe word Hatha means \u201cpower \u201d in Sanskrit, and\u201c ha \u201d is the sun, and \u201cda \u201d refers to the moon. Hatha yoga is practiced to better control the body and achieve physical, mental and spiritual integration, so meditation, breathing exercises, etc., are also important parts of yoga practice.\nAriel said: \u201cModern aerial yoga combines pilate and dance movements, and the movement is beautiful. \u201d Compared to the pursuit of spiritual fit, new yoga, such as aerial yoga, is closer to exercise and can exercise the muscles of the whole body, which is based on the strength of the upper limbs and core muscles.\nJust because the history of aerial yoga is not long, Ariel said that there is still no specific set of \"standard\" actions and processes, and different instructors have different methods and styles of interpretation.\nHigh strength, low muscle strength, foot shock.\nThe aerial yoga posture is very beautiful, so that the beautiful woman who loves to \"punch\" is eager to try, but it is absolutely not low in physical and muscle strength requirements.\nThe common action is to grasp the silk cloth with both hands, using the strength of the arm and back to lift the whole person. \"People with zero movement foundation, when they first started school, they will be very hard, especially women's upper limb strength is usually insufficient, can not support the body, but men learn to have advantages.\"\nSince the whole person is supported by a hammock, it is necessary to have strong core muscle strength to keep the hammock stable, otherwise it is impossible to shake around and complete the action.\nShe stressed that the fancy posture is supported by the arm and abdomen, and the intensity of the exercise is very high. Even if you practice a little or just do a punch, you will be panting after a while.\nAriel said that usually 1 hour novice air yoga session, the instructor will lead the students to do 40 minutes of warm-up stretching, thoroughly stretching the chest, back and leg parts to avoid injury; next about 10 minutes to train the core muscle group, the last 10 minutes to do some more difficult \"punch\" fancy action.\n\"For students who have no basic exercise, 10 minutes of fancy (movement) exercise is enough, for example, when beginners step on a hammock, some people will have a foot shock due to lack of muscle strength.\"\nTherefore, Ariel believes that students have a foundation for exercise, which is helpful for learning aerial yoga.\nAriel says that beginners can start with simple stretching exercises. \u201cHanging bed is like an auxiliary tool to help you do things you can \u2019 t do in normal times, such as inverting. In traditional yoga, it is an advanced movement, but with hanging bed help, new hands can do 1 or 2 lessons. \u201d\nIt's not a good idea to watch a movie and learn by yourself.\nIn the era of Internet development, why not go online and follow the video content to teach yourself, save a tuition fee, and rent yourself a place to play? Ariel said, this idea is not advisable, \"novice definitely not! Aerial yoga has a lot of action, especially fancy, once you do the wrong steps, tense hands will fall from high, the consequences can be very small.\"\nShe suggested that the trainees should have at least half a year of aerial yoga experience, and have a certain foundation to rent a venue for practice.\nIn addition, there are also some safety issues to pay attention to when playing aerial yoga, such as movement, \"aerial yoga has a lot of movement of the body with silk cloth, but try not to tighten joints, such as wrists, elbows, ankles and other positions, otherwise it is easy to sprain.\"\nIn terms of clothing, it is advisable to wear yoga leggings or comfortable sports pants, \"many actions will tighten the thighs and pelvis, to avoid excessive friction between the hammock and the skin, and it is best to have close clothing protection.\"\nText: Shen Qing\nEditor: Lin Hsiao-hui\nFacebook @ Ming Pao Supplement\nHealth Net: Health.\nMingpao.com\nCopyright \u00a9 2019 Mingpao. All Rights Reserved.\nRELATED","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2021-0031.json.gz:36164","uncompressed_offset":254307737,"url":"ol.mingpao.com/ldy/beautystyle/fitness/20211102/1635790348685/%E6%83%B3%E7%8E%A9%E8%8A%B1%E5%BC%8F%E6%89%93%E5%8D%A1-%E5%8A%9B%E9%87%8F%E4%B8%8D%E8%83%BD%E5%B0%8F-%E7%A9%BA%E4%B8%AD%E7%91%9C%E4%BC%BD-%E4%BB%99%E5%A5%B3%E9%9C%80%E7%B7%B4%E8%82%8C","warc_date":"2021-11-03T05:42:13.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:c9efec55-9a18-4405-8637-b047656c1cc8>","warc_url":"https://ol.mingpao.com/ldy/beautystyle/fitness/20211102/1635790348685/%E6%83%B3%E7%8E%A9%E8%8A%B1%E5%BC%8F%E6%89%93%E5%8D%A1-%E5%8A%9B%E9%87%8F%E4%B8%8D%E8%83%BD%E5%B0%8F-%E7%A9%BA%E4%B8%AD%E7%91%9C%E4%BC%BD-%E4%BB%99%E5%A5%B3%E9%9C%80%E7%B7%B4%E8%82%8C"},"created":"2021-11-03T05:58:59.000Z","lang":"eng"},"7c9126d4-1629-4a1a-aa4d-03a9c622b034_296262592":{"id":"7c9126d4-1629-4a1a-aa4d-03a9c622b034_296262592","text":"6 myths about yoga: dispel and start practicing\n28 September 2021, 16: 47\nRead news in ukrainian\nSource:\nEveryday Health\nYoga is not only about physical exertion, but also about relieving stress and peace.\nRegular classes will help to get in shape, improve mood and give a lot of energy.\nYoga Alliance says that yoga is suitable for many and is a universal occupation.\nIt will help relieve pain, give strength and flexibility, relieve stress, improve breathing, the cardiovascular system, help lose weight and promote better circulation.\nIf you still doubted about this way of recovery and rest, we will dispel them in our material.\nWhat danger lies in wait for children in the sandbox\n6 myths about yoga\nI'm not flexible.\nOften, professional yogis on social networks demonstrate the incredible flexibility of their body in various exercises.\nThis raises doubts about whether it is suitable for those who do not consider themselves flexible at all and have never heard of stretching.\nIn fact, yoga begins with light exercises that everyone is able to repeat.\nOver time, they can become more difficult, and you will develop.\nIn addition, exercises can be replaced if some can not be repeated.\nYou don \u2019 t have to be flexible to practice yoga / Photo Unsplash\nMy back hurts.\nPain should not interfere with you both at work and during yoga classes.\nThat is why there are many different practices for almost every medical condition.\nIf you are worried about some disease, consult your doctor before signing up for classes, and do not forget to warn the coach so that he can choose individual exercises for you.\nFor example, if you have glaucoma (a disease that damages the optic nerves of the eyes), you need to avoid lowering your head below the heart, which means that you will have to change certain poses.\n\u2013 explains Samantha Parker, a physiologist and certified yoga instructor.\nIt may be against my religious beliefs.\nYou can focus only on exercises / Photo Unsplash\nYoga is often associated with Hinduism and Buddhism, but it does not require certain religious beliefs and can be practiced by everyone.\nIt only propagates the idea of peace and purpose, which some people identify with spirituality.\nIf this is not very close to you, you can find appropriate classes where instructors focus exclusively on physical aspects.\nYoga for women\nAccording to the 2016 Yoga in America study, 72% of participants were women and 28% were men.\nHowever, this trend is changing every year.\nYoga is a universal practice that helps everyone to improve joint mobility, range of motion and overall physical fitness.\nIn addition, it contributes to good posture, control of muscles and tendons.\nYoga is suitable for women and men / Photo Unsplash\nYoga is just a stretch.\nYoga is often about the emphasis on flexibility, because it involves a lot of stretch marks.\nHowever, along with mobility, you build muscle and stamina.\nThe study, published in the journal Research Complementary and Alternative Medicine, described that a 12-week yoga program improved not only flexibility, but also cardiovascular, muscle strength, and endurance in adults.\nWhy you can not lose weight: nutritionists called 5 common mistakes\nI don 't have time\nEven short classes will improve well-being / Photo Unsplash\nYou have time, you just spend it doing other things,\nThis is Samantha Parker.\nYoga does not require a specific time to practice.\nYou can choose the duration and load on your own.\nLong classes will bring more benefits, but even short practices will help relieve excessive tension and give a good mood.","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2021-0028.json.gz:27055","uncompressed_offset":296262592,"url":"zdorovo.24tv.ua/ru/6-mifov-o-joge-razveivaem-nachinaem-zanimatsja_n1751067/amp","warc_date":"2021-09-28T19:15:50.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:7c9126d4-1629-4a1a-aa4d-03a9c622b034>","warc_url":"https://zdorovo.24tv.ua/ru/6-mifov-o-joge-razveivaem-nachinaem-zanimatsja_n1751067/amp"},"created":"2021-09-28T19:32:38.000Z","lang":"eng"},"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":{"id":"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054","text":"Women's Health\nJul 14th, 2022\n| | | |\nIn recent years, yoga has become a major trend, and there are constantly new large-scale yoga centers or small and exquisite yoga studios opening, and sports brands have also launched high-quality yoga clothing, which shows that yoga is becoming increasingly popular.\nAccording to the statistics of yoga journals, most of the readers and practitioners of yoga are also women, in fact, in ancient Indian culture, yoga only passed on men but not women.\nHowever, since the popularity of yoga culture, on the contrary, more women like the physical and mental benefits of yoga, of course, after exercise can have a better body line is also the majority of people want to pursue.\nBenefits of Yoga Practice for Women in Growth\nYoga practice for women in the process of growing up better preparation, female hormones with the onset of puberty menstruation, to pregnancy, and then to menopause, different stages of the body will change and practice yoga can make physical and psychological easier to adapt and face.\nPregnancy can be said to be a turning point in a girl \u2019 s life, physical and physical changes and the joy and challenges brought by meeting new life, the psychological face a lot of pressure, emotional is also vulnerable to hormonal influence and become unstable.\nPrenatal and postnatal yoga practice, in addition to a series of special styles, will also include breathing and meditation meditation meditation, these exercises can reduce or even avoid prenatal and postnatal depression or emotional problems, and the body can recover relatively quickly.\nImpact of Women's Health\nIn addition to changes during pregnancy, female health is also vulnerable to life or work pressure, and poor eating habits.\nCommon common female health problems such as hormonal disorders, anemia, gynecological problems, emotional disorders or depression.\nBreast cancer, cervical cancer is also the most common chronic disease in women.\nIn the United States, women die of breast cancer second only to lung cancer.\nAccording to the World Health Organization \u2019 s 2020 report, 2.3 million women worldwide have been diagnosed with breast cancer and 685,000 have died from it.\nIt was also noted that 7.8 million women had been diagnosed with breast cancer between 2015 and 2020, making it one of the most prevalent cancers in the world. (https: / / www.who.int / news-room / fact-sheets / detail / breastcancer)\nBenefits of Yoga for Cancer Treatment\nYoga Alliance has conducted more than 150 clinical trials on the benefits of yoga for cancer treatment, involving more than 10,000 patients.\nMost of these studies have focused on breast cancer, reflecting the prevalence of breast cancer.\nThe clinical trial looked at a group of female breast cancer survivors from around the world who practiced yoga, including routines, breathing routines, relaxation and meditation.\nStudies have shown that these elements of practice contribute to improved overall health, emotional relief, deeper spiritual connections, and a clearer sense of purpose and meaning in life.\nAfter cancer diagnosis and treatment, especially after surgery and chemotherapy, there are often many side effects, such as lymphatic swelling, easy edema, muscle and bone pain, easy fatigue, decreased immunity, cognitive decline, poor sleep quality and even insomnia, anxiety and depression.\nAccording to the Yoga Alliance report, it lasts 4-24 weeks, and regularly practices 1-3 classes and exercises at home every week.\nMultiple clinical studies have shown that yoga is safe and effective for breast cancer patients or survivors.\nBecause of the large number of breast cancer survivors involved in this clinical study, the results are sufficient to support the effectiveness and benefits of yoga therapy in breast cancer treatment, oncologists in the United States and Europe also recommend yoga therapy for breast cancer patients during their illness and recovery.\nEspecially for reducing stress, anxiety, depression, fatigue, improve sleep quality, cognitive impairment, and help to reduce cancer related sequelae.\nStudies have also shown that yoga improves inflammation and immune function derived from breast cancer.\nAmong them, for patients who have undergone chemotherapy and radiation therapy, yoga effectively reduces their pain, muscle and arm discomfort during treatment.\nAfter practicing yoga, it can also reduce lymphoedema, joint and muscle fibrosis changes, increase the range of activities and ability, improve the quality of daily life and mental health.\nThrough the continuous practice of yoga and breathing, it can enhance and strengthen the function of the internal organs, stimulate and help balance the endocrine, relieve symptoms and improve the condition.\nRespiratory breathing can effectively manage pain, so that patients can relax, maintain mindfulness, and recover in a shorter time.\nHere are some exercises for breast cancer patients and survivors:\nYoga Practice\nCat Pose\nIt is one of the most common and common forms of practice.\nPractice cat style can improve the activity of the spine and overall flexibility, and stimulate the secretion of the spinal cord, improve and balance the secretion of hormones in the body.\nFish Pose\nIt is recommended to practice more in recovery.\nPlace the yoga brick in the middle of the back and slowly lie down.\nAfter mastectomy, patients will feel pain in the upper chest and upper arm, and joint activity is limited.\nFish helps relieve stiffness in the shoulders, chest, and upper back.\nSome patients may experience shortness of breath and difficulty breathing after treatment due to chest muscle tension and pain. Fish can help improve breathing volume.\nBreathing and calming exercises\nNadi Shodhana alternative nostril breathing method\nImpress diaphragmatic movements to stimulate nerve reflexes, help calm the body and mind, improve sleep quality, and balance the yin and yang energy balance.\nPracticing breathing meditation can relieve emotional problems such as anxiety and stress and effectively manage pain.\nRelaxation and mindfulness meditation practice\nYoga Nidra Sleep Yoga\nIt helps release tension, stress and anxiety to relieve pain, strengthen self-awareness and physical connection, improve sleep quality, and maintain peace of mind and mindfulness.\nYoga has been practiced for thousands of years, and has been validated by modern scientific research, which has found that yoga therapy is conducive to the spiritual practice of mind and body.\nPracticing yoga has many health benefits that women can use throughout their lives.\nAsana Journal\nBio\nAsana International Yoga Journal\nShare This Story, Choose Your Platform!","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2022-0022.json.gz:23820","uncompressed_offset":586310054,"url":"www.asanajournal.com/%E5%A5%B3%E6%80%A7%E5%81%A5%E5%BA%B7/","warc_date":"2022-07-28T06:00:49.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926>","warc_url":"https://www.asanajournal.com/%E5%A5%B3%E6%80%A7%E5%81%A5%E5%BA%B7/"},"created":"2022-07-28T06:40:00.000Z","lang":"eng"},"7ce46cae-7773-42c9-b947-29f1dcc32eac_54150723":{"id":"7ce46cae-7773-42c9-b947-29f1dcc32eac_54150723","text":"Yoga | Want to do Coffee Lin Qianyu 2.0? Which way is right for yourself?\nSee your own practice.\nAuthor: The Doctor Easy\nPublished: Updated:\nMore and more people pay attention to health and exercise in their spare time.\nIn addition to outdoor sports such as hiking and running, many indoor sports have also emerged, of which yoga is the most popular.\nSome simple yoga exercises can also be practiced at home.\nIn fact, there are many types of yoga, in addition to the usual air yoga, there are detox yoga, gentle yoga, etc., suitable for different people.\nThis article will introduce a variety of common types of yoga, help readers to choose the right type of yoga according to their physical condition and spiritual needs, and learn how yoga centers can help users training.\nIn fact, there are many types of yoga, in addition to the usual air yoga, there are also detoxification yoga, gentle yoga, etc., suitable for different people. (Photo: Courtesy of the respondent)\nAerial Yoga and Yoga Wheel Exercises Need Assistive Tools to Improve Urban Pain\nLet \u2019 s introduce two types of yoga that have emerged in recent years and require assistive devices, namely \u201cAerial Yoga \u201d and\u201c Yoga Wheel \u201d.\nWhen it comes to the most popular type of yoga, it must be Aerial Yoga.\nAerial yoga, also known as \u201canti-gravity yoga \u201d, practitioners suspended their bodies through a hanging cloth hammock hanging from the ceiling, allowing the body to maintain balance and stay in mid-air under the influence of gravity. It is suitable for people who want to train core muscles, balance, improve the body \u2019 s sense of coordination and softness, and enhance hand grip and muscle strength.\nAerial yoga can significantly increase blood circulation, and the practice process will often \"burst sweat\", which is quite relaxing; among them, the movement of air inversion has a traction effect, which can have a physiological effect on the spine.\nThe practice of aerial yoga tends to \"sweat\", which is quite relaxing; it is also suitable for women who want to improve their posture to put out a variety of beautiful positions in the air.\n(Photo: Courtesy of the interviewee)\nYoga Wheel is a class of yoga classes conducted on the ground. The yoga wheel is like a hollow wheel, which is used to expand the stretching space, assist the balance of the back bend, and so on.\nThe use of yoga wheels for posterior curvature allows the spine to get more space for stretching, strengthening the stretching of the chest muscles and waist muscles, thereby increasing lung capacity and enhancing cardiopulmonary function.\nThe biggest attraction of yoga wheels is the ability to specifically improve shoulder and neck pain, camel back, and waist tightness.\nThe use of yoga wheels for back bending allows the spine to get more space to stretch, which can specifically improve the shoulder and neck pain, camel back, waist tightening and other problems.\n(Photo: Courtesy of the interviewee)\nHatha Yoga focuses on breathing and extends many branches\nHatha Yoga is the oldest and most widely practiced form of yoga. \u201cHatha \u201d is Sanskrit, meaning\u201c power \u201d.\nHatha Yoga is a combination of breathing, dark thoughts and asanas. The purpose of the practice is to purify the spirit by mastering the body, and ultimately connect to spirituality.\nDifferent body styles can effectively coordinate different parts of the bones and muscles, and help promote blood circulation throughout the body, while breathing can effectively increase lung capacity.\nPractice Hatha Yoga with an emphasis on controlling your breathing and focusing on feeling each position without having to obsess over making the perfect posture.\nThe practitioner calms the mind, calms the mind, and boosts the spirit.\nVarious types of yoga extended by Hatha Yoga, such as gentle yoga, yin yoga, detoxification yoga, yoga therapy, etc., have more targeted effects.\nPractice Hatha Yoga with an emphasis on controlling your breathing and focusing on feeling each position without obsessing over making perfect postures. (Photo: Courtesy of the interviewee)\nVarious branches of Hatha Yoga, from mind to physiotherapy, suitable for different needs\nGentle Yoga focuses on stretching and breathing, not on extreme flexibility or strength.\nBody style includes sitting stretching, standing posture, forward bending and low impact back bending exercises.\nFor people with zero basics, gentle yoga is the best starting choice.\nYin Yoga, which focuses on meditation and meditation, is a \u201cpassive \u201d practice. The essence is to\u201c give in \u201d, learn how to let go of the struggle and allow things to happen naturally, so that the practitioner can calm his mind and gain more powerful mental energy.\nEach session lasts about three to five minutes, which is longer than other types of yoga, and assistive devices can be used to support the longer session.\nSince there is no standing posture in Yin Yoga, the practice focuses on the pelvis, hip, lower abdomen, spine and other parts, which can enhance the softness of the lower body and promote blood circulation, especially for women and pregnant women.\nYin Yoga focuses on meditation and meditation, and each style lasts about three to five minutes, which is longer than other yoga types.\n(Photo: Courtesy of the interviewee)\nDetox yoga focuses on systematically stretching and compressing every part of the body.\nThe body consists of pushing, pulling, twisting, squeezing and stretching.\nThese actions can stimulate some organs with detoxification function. They help the body to expel toxins and unnecessary substances to achieve detoxification and slimming effects.\nDetox yoga focuses on systematically stretching and compressing every part of the body, which can stimulate some organs with detoxification function, helping the body to expel toxins and unnecessary substances to achieve detoxification and slimming effects.\n(Photo: Courtesy of the interviewee)\nYoga Physical is the application of yoga practice to treatment, by combining the human meridian and yoga movements, thereby promoting blood circulation, adjusting metabolism, improving the function of body parts, and achieving the purpose of relieving pain.\nDepending on the area you want to improve, such as shoulders and neck, pelvis, legs and hips, the posture of each yoga session may vary.\nTriAngel Yoga was founded by experienced yoga instructors.\nSome of the types of yoga mentioned above can be practiced on their own, but if you want to focus on the types of yoga, you need to have professional guidance. TriAngel Yoga is founded by experienced yoga teachers and has a variety of learning modes, suitable for different levels of practitioners.\nTake Aerial Yoga as an example, although there are many challenging styles, but the teacher will gradually guide the beginners, with ease, pleasure, stress reduction, and self-confidence as the focus of the class.\nIn terms of Hatha Yoga, the classes at TriAngel Yoga will arrange different types of mats to suit different needs, such as strengthening muscles, increasing body coordination, improving poor posture, improving flexibility, improving concentration, reducing stress and relaxation, detoxification, and increasing self-confidence.\nWith professional guidance, you can avoid injury and learn the correct posture.\nFor Hatha Yoga, the classes at TriAngel Yoga will be organized according to different types of topics, with different styles of mats to suit different needs. (Photo: freepik)\nYou may be interested","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2022-0011.json.gz:38065","uncompressed_offset":54150723,"url":"www.hk01.com/%E9%86%AB%E5%B8%ABEasy/733580/%E7%91%9C%E4%BC%BD-%E6%83%B3%E5%81%9Acoffee%E6%9E%97%E8%8A%8A%E5%A6%A42-0-%E5%93%AA%E7%A8%AE%E6%96%B9%E5%BC%8F%E5%95%B1%E8%87%AA%E5%B7%B1-%E5%8D%B3%E7%9D%87%E9%81%A9%E5%90%88%E8%87%AA%E5%B7%B1%E7%9A%84%E7%B7%B4%E7%BF%92","warc_date":"2022-04-22T04:18:07.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:7ce46cae-7773-42c9-b947-29f1dcc32eac>","warc_url":"https://www.hk01.com/%E9%86%AB%E5%B8%ABEasy/733580/%E7%91%9C%E4%BC%BD-%E6%83%B3%E5%81%9Acoffee%E6%9E%97%E8%8A%8A%E5%A6%A42-0-%E5%93%AA%E7%A8%AE%E6%96%B9%E5%BC%8F%E5%95%B1%E8%87%AA%E5%B7%B1-%E5%8D%B3%E7%9D%87%E9%81%A9%E5%90%88%E8%87%AA%E5%B7%B1%E7%9A%84%E7%B7%B4%E7%BF%92"},"created":"2022-04-22T04:20:25.000Z","lang":"eng"},"cb0bfd59-0204-48ce-8ed9-e9ae5b423d81_785624450":{"id":"cb0bfd59-0204-48ce-8ed9-e9ae5b423d81_785624450","text":"What streets will be closed in Moscow on July 9-10\nMoscow 24\nSport\n09: 01\nHome / Stories /\nFitness expert told who can benefit from training in the style of Animal Flow\nFluttering like a butterfly: how effective is Animal Flow training\nMoscow 24 columnist and TV presenter Eduard Kanevsky told about a new direction in fitness, copying the movement of animals, Animal Flow.\nPhoto: depositphotos / baranq\nThe modern fitness industry does not cease to offer its customers more and more new directions of training.\nMany position them as something unique, giving a truly excellent result and, of course, in a short time.\nThis is a normal phenomenon for the sports industry, because the consumer always needs something new.\nIn particular, it is necessary to diversify the training process or to save time.\nGuided by a similar principle, the famous fitness trainer Michael Fitchel developed and integrated Animal Flow training into his classes.\nThis is a set of exercises that are aimed at copying the movements of various animals - crab, scorpion, chimpanzee and so on.\nThe advantage of this technique is that you work with your own body weight, and for the exercises themselves you only need a mat.\nSuch training can be carried out anywhere in the world, both online with a coach, and independently.\nAnother advantage is that each person can pick up movements for himself, depending on the level of training.\nThe training itself does not look easy, as it may seem from the outside.\nThe main principle of the program is that the change of positions is without interruption, which significantly increases the overall load on the body.\nIt would seem that this is a really interesting, new direction that allows you to work out all the muscles of the body, plus burn excess calories.\nBut is there a downside to Animal Flow?\nLet's figure it out.\nTo begin with, calling the method unique, unfortunately, will not work.\nAfter all, most movements are present in Pilates and yoga.\nThe second significant disadvantage is that many exercises require not only considerable agility and strength, but also stretching, as well as mobility in the joints.\nBut the older the person, the more difficult it will be for him to master this or that pose.\nIt's not easy here at all.\nAlmost every second person over the age of 25 has problems with the spine.\nTherefore, when trying to take a certain \"animal\" position, an injury may occur.\nMoreover, damage to the back, joints, tendon sprains are a frequent consequence of yoga, especially when a person tries to master asanas (poses in yoga) on their own.\nJust here lies the main drawback of the Michael Fitchel technique: you can learn to engage in this direction only in the presence of a highly qualified coach.\nOtherwise, both the safety of training and its effectiveness are called into question.\nIn fact, this applies to all fitness.\nPhoto: depositphotos / stockasso\nTake, for example, the good old gym, which is absolutely in any club.\nThe number of injuries that beginners who decide to independently master the technique of performing exercises receive is simply off the scale.\nAlthough they were sure that there was nothing easier than to squat with a barbell or make deadlift.\nThe same applies to the correctly selected sequence of exercises, the choice of load, as well as rest between workouts in general.\nFor all this, it is important to consider the goals and objectives of a particular person\nTherefore, to master the new methodology Animal Flow necessarily need a coach, and also - the absence of any restrictions on health.\nAs far as I know, this direction has not yet been presented in Moscow, but I am sure that major network players will be happy to integrate this lesson into their clubs.\nBut that's not all.\nYou need to understand that such a system of exercises is just a variation on the topic of functional training.\nThese are classes that are aimed at the simultaneous development of endurance, flexibility, strength, coordination and so on.\nBut no such complex, except for crossfit, will not give you the opportunity, for example, to gain a good developed muscle mass.\nTo do this, you need not your own body weight, but an additional load in the form of weights.\nSo, being in the position of \"crab\", you do not pump up the buttocks.\nThe same applies to those who expect with the help of such training to lose weight by reducing body fat.\nUnfortunately, no matter how hard you practice, during exercise, the body uses only sugar (glycogen) as an energy source, but not subcutaneous fat.\nThe necessary conditions are not created for its combustion.\nTherefore, those who want to lose extra pounds will have to add aerobic training.\nIt is easy to conclude that there are no unique methods or even diets.\nAll that is associated with a good result is a complex of trainings with different types of load and correctly selected exercises.\nTrying something new is always a good thing.\nJust never count on a miracle, which in this case simply will not happen.\nclose\nContact Us\nFeedback form\nAttach file\nSend\nFollow the news:\nNo more showing","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2022-0020.json.gz:143679","uncompressed_offset":785624450,"url":"www.m24.ru/articles/sport/10072022/479428","warc_date":"2022-07-10T17:03:54.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:cb0bfd59-0204-48ce-8ed9-e9ae5b423d81>","warc_url":"https://www.m24.ru/articles/sport/10072022/479428"},"created":"2022-07-10T18:02:19.000Z","lang":"eng"},"156128be-4d9b-4d64-9015-c1e3c17c590c_23808005":{"id":"156128be-4d9b-4d64-9015-c1e3c17c590c_23808005","text":"01/8\u200bWhat are some yoga poses that are inspired by animals?\n\nYoga is more than just a physical exercise; it\u2019s a way to connect with nature, both internally and externally. Some of the most effective and beneficial yoga poses are inspired by the animal kingdom. These poses, named after various animals, not only mimic their movements but also carry their qualities and benefits. Here are 7 yoga poses inspired by animals that can help us tap into our inner strength, flexibility, and inner strength.\n\nreadmore\n\n02/8\u200bFish pose (Matsyasana)\n\nThe Fish pose, or Matsyasana, mimics the form of a fish swimming in water. This pose is known for its ability to open up the chest and throat, promoting deep breathing and relaxation. Lifting your heart towards the sky, stimulates the thyroid and parathyroid glands, balancing hormones and boosting metabolism.\n\nA study published in the International Journal of Yoga found that practising Matsyasana significantly improves respiratory function and lung capacity. This makes it particularly beneficial for individuals dealing with respiratory issues or those looking to enhance their breathing during meditation or physical activities.\n\nHow to do it:\n\n1. Lie on your back with your legs extended and feet together.\n\n2. Place your hands underneath your hips, palms down.\n\n3. Lift your chest and arch your back, tilting your head back so the crown of your head touches the floor.\n\n4. Hold for a few breaths, then slowly release.\n\nreadmore\n\n03/8\u200bCobra pose (Bhujangasana)\n\nCobra pose, or Bhujangasana, copies the poised and powerful cobra ready to strike. This pose is excellent for strengthening the spine and opening the chest, enhancing flexibility and alleviating stress.\n\nResearch conducted by the Journal of Physical Therapy Science demonstrated that Bhujangasana significantly reduces lower back pain and improves spinal alignment. The pose stimulates the digestive organs, aiding in digestion and reducing bloating.\n\nHow to practice\n\n1. Lie on your stomach with your hands under your shoulders.\n\n2. Press into your hands to lift your chest off the ground, keeping your elbows close to your body.\n\n3. Look up slightly, keeping your neck long.\n\n4. Hold for a few breaths before lowering back down.\n\nreadmore\n\n04/8\u200bCow Face pose (Gomukhasana)\n\nGomukhasana, or Cow Face pose, takes its name from the serene and sacred cow, a symbol of calmness and gentleness in many cultures. This pose is particularly effective for stretching the hips, thighs, and shoulders, helping to alleviate stiffness and improve flexibility.\n\nAccording to a study in the Journal of Bodywork and Movement Therapies, regular practice of Gomukhasana helps reduce symptoms of anxiety and depression by promoting physical relaxation and mental calmness.\n\nHow to practice\n\n1. Sit on the floor with your legs extended.\n\n2. Cross your right leg over your left, stacking your knees.\n\n3. Reach your right arm behind your back and your left arm over your shoulder, clasping your hands.\n\n4. Hold for a few breaths and then switch sides.\n\nreadmore\n\n05/8\u200bDownward-Facing Dog pose (Adho Mukha Svanasana)\n\nDownward-Facing Dog, or Adho Mukha Svanasana, is one of the most recognisable yoga poses, imitating a dog stretching its body. This pose is excellent for stretching the hamstrings, calves, and spine while also strengthening the arms and legs.\n\nA study published in the Journal of Exercise Rehabilitation revealed that practising Downward-Facing Dog can enhance overall flexibility and improve blood circulation, which is crucial for maintaining cardiovascular health.\n\nHow to practice\n\n1. Start on your hands and knees, with your wrists under your shoulders and knees under your hips.\n\n2. Lift your hips towards the ceiling, straightening your legs and creating an inverted V shape.\n\n3. Press your heels towards the floor and hold for a few breaths.\n\nreadmore\n\n06/8\u200bButterfly pose (Badhakonasana)\n\nThe Butterfly Pose, or Badhakonasana, is inspired by the gentle and graceful butterfly. This pose is excellent for opening the hips and groin area, which can help improve flexibility and relieve tension.\n\nResearch in the Indian Journal of Medical Research indicates that Badhakonasana can aid in improving posture and reducing discomfort related to menstrual cycles. It\u2019s also beneficial for stretching the inner thighs and promoting a sense of relaxation.\n\nHow to do it:\n\n1. Sit on the floor and bring the soles of your feet together, allowing your knees to fall out to the sides.\n\n2. Hold your feet with your hands and gently press your knees towards the floor.\n\n3. Hold for a few breaths, feeling a stretch in your inner thighs.\n\nreadmore\n\n07/8\u200bCat stretch (Marjariasana)\n\nMarjariasana, or Cat stretch, mimics the fluid and flexible movements of a cat. This pose is great for enhancing spinal flexibility and relieving tension in the back.\n\nThe Cat Stretch can help alleviate back pain and improve overall spinal health by encouraging gentle movement and stretching.\n\nHow to practice\n\n1. Start on your hands and knees, with your wrists under your shoulders and knees under your hips.\n\n2. Arch your back towards the ceiling, tucking your chin to your chest.\n\n3. Then, drop your belly towards the floor, lifting your head and tailbone.\n\n4. Continue to flow between these two positions for a few breaths.\n\n\n(Images: Canva)\n\nreadmore\n\n08/8\u200bDolphin Plank pose (Makara Adho Mukha Svanasana)\n\nThis pose channels the sleek and powerful dolphin. This pose is a fantastic core strengthener, engaging the abdominal muscles and building endurance.\n\nA study from the Journal of Strength and Conditioning Research shows that poses like Dolphin Plank can significantly improve core stability and strength, which is vital for overall body balance and injury prevention.\n\nHow to practice\n\n1. Start in a forearm plank position, with your elbows under your shoulders and your body in a straight line.\n\n2. Engage your core and hold for a few breaths, keeping your body stable and strong.\n\nreadmore","url":"https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/life-style/health-fitness/fitness/natural-wisdom-7-yoga-poses-inspired-by-animals-that-work-like-magic/photostory/110992889.cms"}}}
