e characteristics and intelligence have made them a favorite among dog owners."},{"citations":{"7b7063fa-c3ab-47ba-a6df-d62fc9c7e481_363892899":1.0},"text":"As the breed continues to grow in popularity, it is essential to remember the importance of providing corgis with the mental and physical stimulation they need to thrive."}],"answer":[{"citations":{},"text":"The popularity of corgis as a beloved breed can be attributed to the historical bond between the royal family and the breed, with Queen Elizabeth II playing a central role in making them a household name."},{"citations":{},"text":"According to various sources, including [4a6f8b30-e1d2-4503-a54c-4842176faffd_760865987], the queen's love for corgis began when her parents welcomed the family's first corgi, Dookie, in 1933, and she was later gifted a corgi named Susan for her 18th birthday in 1944."},{"citations":{"0f582f8d-3aa3-47f1-9bbb-4cfcd595c3de_891736516":1.0},"text":"This marked the beginning of the royal line of corgis, with all subsequent royal corgis bred by the monarch descending from Susan, the original."},{"citations":{"4a6f8b30-e1d2-4503-a54c-4842176faffd_760865987":1.0},"text":"The queen's fondness for corgis was due to their \"energy and untamed spirit\", as reported by Reader's Digest."},{"citations":{"4a6f8b30-e1d2-4503-a54c-4842176faffd_760865987":1.0},"text":"Over the years, the queen's association with corgis has been well-documented, with numerous photos and stories featuring her with her beloved pets, including a notable instance where her corgi, Susan, accompanied her on her honeymoon and gave birth to a pair of puppies in 1949."},{"citations":{"23cd6320-dc30-49bb-b11d-4e573e59f6db_380264552":1.0},"text":"The queen's love for corgis has had a significant impact on the breed's popularity, with the Kennel Club crediting her as the major factor in making them one of the UK's most popular breeds today."},{"citations":{"23cd6320-dc30-49bb-b11d-4e573e59f6db_380264552":1.0},"text":"In fact, the