f air leakage from the International Space Station.\nAccording to the information office, the materials and equipment needed to repair this place will be sent aboard the Progress cargo vehicle.\n\"The equipment and materials necessary to stop air leakage will be sent with the first Progress cargo vehicle launched to the International Space Station, to solve this problem once and for all,\" the statement said.\nAstronauts Peter Dobrov and Anton Shkaplerov discovered the possible location of the air leak in December in the middle chamber of the Zvezda unit.\nNASA has said it is considering isolating the Zvezda module completely if necessary.\nThe Roscosmos media office commented: \u201cThe concerns of our partners are unfounded and surprising. \u201d\nSource: Novosti\nAgree.\nThis website uses cookies. You can read the terms of use to activate this feature by clicking here","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2022-0001.json.gz:51762","uncompressed_offset":449949310,"url":"arabic.rt.com/space/1315808-%D8%A7%D9%83%D8%AA%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%81-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%AA%D9%85%D9%84-%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B3%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%87%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%B7%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D8%B6%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A9/","warc_date":"2022-01-19T11:00:43.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:d0632052-f69f-43bf-95b7-ca2758d8a9ee>","warc_url":"https://arabic.rt.com/space/1315808-%D8%A7%D9%83%D8%AA%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%81-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%AA%D9%85%D9%84-%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B3%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%87%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%B7%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D8%B6%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A9/"},"created":"2022-01-19T11:23:42.000Z","lang":"eng"},"715ac48a-c2b6-4220-ba56-bebfa9774221_734447027":{"id":"715ac48a-c2b6-4220-ba56-bebfa9774221_734447027","text":"NEWS\nNEWS\nFebruary 28, 20: 41\nScience\nRoscosmos reported air leakage on the Russian segment of the ISS\nPhoto: telegram channel \"State Corporation\" Roscosmos \"\nAir leakage occurred on the Russian segment of the ISS, the crew and the station itself is not threatened.\nThis writes TASS with reference to the press service of Roscosmos.\n\u201cIndeed, experts fix the leakage of air on board the ISS.\nThe crew regularly carries out work to find and eliminate possible leakage sites, and the data coming from the station are transmitted for analysis to specialists in the normal mode, \u201d the state corporation said.\nAccording to \"Interfax\" with reference to the head of the NASA program on the ISS Joel Montalbano, the leak is observed in the tail part of the ISS.\n\u201cWe saw that the leak increased about a week before the last launch of Progress and its docking with the station, \u201d he said.\nThe head of the NASA program on the ISS said that the air in the transition chamber of the Zvezda module began to leave twice as fast.\nAccording to Montalbano, experts are in contact with Russian colleagues on the next steps.\nHowever, this situation does not affect the safety of the crew, he said.\nLast year, Russian cosmonauts Oleg Kononenko and Nikolai Chub in outer space disconnected the faulty circuit of the additional radiator on the module \"Science\" from the main circuit of the module.\nBefore that, they went into outer space, opening the exit hatch of the module \"Search\" of the International Space Station.\nMore news \u2014 in the telegram channel Moscow 24 Subscribe!\nclose\nContact Us\nFeedback form\nAttach file\nSend\nclose","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2024-0005.json.gz:179153","uncompressed_offset":734447027,"url":"www.m24.ru/news/nauka/28022024/670105","warc_date":"2024-02-29T07:17:46.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:715ac48a-c2b6-4220-ba56-bebfa9774221>","warc_url":"https://www.m24.ru/news/nauka/28022024/670105"},"created":"2024-02-29T08:10:09.000Z","lang":"eng"},"4d07b9d8-1eb3-4ebe-aaf2-39e5725dc367_682748788":{"id":"4d07b9d8-1eb3-4ebe-aaf2-39e5725dc367_682748788","text":"29 Feb, 2024 11:18\n\nRussia comments on space station leak\n\nA NASA official had previously reported that air loss from the Zvezda module had doubled\n\nAir leaking from a segment of the International Space Station (ISS) poses no risk to its crew or the orbital outpost, the Russian space agency Roscosmos has said.\n\nA NASA official had previously reported that the rate at which air was escaping from the satellite's Russian Zvezda module under certain circumstances had doubled. The situation is under control and being constantly monitored, the\u00a0Roscosmos told Interfax on Wednesday, when asked about remarks by NASA\u2019s ISS program manager,\u00a0Joel Montalbano,.\n\n\u201dThe aging of the station\u2019s structure and the growing need for repair and maintenance work on board require a significant portion of the crew\u2019s time,\u201d Roscosmos said.\n\nMontalbano mentioned the issue during this week\u2019s briefing on the upcoming SpaceX Crew-8 mission, which is scheduled for launch on Friday.\n\n\u201dThere is an area in the aft end of the International Space Station. [There is] a small leak. We\u2019ve seen this leak increase about a week before the recent Progress launch and docking,\u201d he said, referring to a Russian automatic supply freighter.\n\nThe volume of lost air has increased to about two pounds a day, compared to a pound a day previously, Montalbano said.\n\n\u201dThe hatch is closed in that area. It\u2019s not an impact on Crew-8, but I didn\u2019t want anyone to be surprised, if they hear about that later,\u201d he explained.\n\nThe use of the module for retrieving the Progress shipment didn\u2019t pose any issues in terms of the leak, he said. The next opening of the hatch is expected in April. While it\u2019s closed, the rest of the station is \u201csolid.\u201d\n\nTechnical issues at the ISS are being reported on a regular basis. Roscosmos has said the age of the station is a key reason why it is developing plans for a new purely Russian-manned orbital structure as an alternative to participating in the international project.\n\nPodcasts\n0:00\n27:58\n0:00\n26:56","url":"https://www.rt.com/news/593386-nasa-roscosmos-iss-leak/"},"7fffb776-5030-474f-b10c-da40f37e1b1f_276131129":{"id":"7fffb776-5030-474f-b10c-da40f37e1b1f_276131129","text":"Ribbon\n01 January 07: 01\nAll news\nvk.com / Cosmonaut Ivan Wagner\nMoscow, January 1.\nRussian cosmonauts Pyotr Dubrov and Anton Shkaplerov discovered in the Zvezda module on the International Space Station, presumably the last place of air leakage.\nThis was reported in the press service of Roscosmos.\nThe first small leak was discovered on the ISS back in 2019, since then, astronauts have been monitoring the situation and eliminating cracks in the hull.\nExperts know how to return the module tightness.\nThis will be done as soon as Progress delivers the necessary equipment to orbit.\n\u201cRussian cosmonauts Peter Dubrov and Anton Shkaplerov found a possible last place of air leakage in the intermediate chamber of the service module\u201c Star \u201d of the Russian segment of the ISS \u201d, \u2014 stated in the message.\nRussian President Vladimir Putin previously admitted the possibility of continuing the operation of the ISS after 2024.\nThis is necessary to maintain high launch activity.\nGo back\nComment","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2022-0000.json.gz:1629","uncompressed_offset":276131129,"url":"riafan.ru/1580987-roskosmos-soobshchil-ob-obnaruzhenii-vozmozhnogo-poslednego-mesta-utechki-vozduha-na-mks","warc_date":"2022-01-01T03:16:44.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:7fffb776-5030-474f-b10c-da40f37e1b1f>","warc_url":"https://riafan.ru/1580987-roskosmos-soobshchil-ob-obnaruzhenii-vozmozhnogo-poslednego-mesta-utechki-vozduha-na-mks"},"created":"2022-01-01T04:01:40.000Z","lang":"eng"},"0a040a3e-2812-41a4-9857-45bdf81b5e75_113364068":{"id":"0a040a3e-2812-41a4-9857-45bdf81b5e75_113364068","text":"Soyuz manufacturing defect causes air leak at International Space Station\nKazakhstan News Agency / Astana / September 3 - According to the Russian satellite network reported on the 3rd, Russian rocket space sources said that the manufacturing defect is the cause of the \"Soyuz MS-09\" spacecraft leak.\nThere was an air leak on the International Space Station on August 30.\nThe astronauts examined all the compartments and found tiny cracks in the Soyuz MS-09 spacecraft.\nIt is located in the living module, not in the return module, so it will not affect the return of the spacecraft to Earth.\nIt was previously thought that the fissure was the result of a miniature meteorite hitting the spacecraft.\nThe next night, Russian cosmonauts used special sealant to fill the hole.\nThe source said: \"The cause of the crack in the inner shell of the living module has been identified and it has appeared on Earth.\nThe person responsible for the fault was identified. \"\nAccording to another source, the crew likely sealed the leak with special glue after realizing the mistake, so it was not detected during the pre-launch check and the spacecraft \u2019 s first two months of orbital flight.\n\"However, the glue later dried out and was squeezed out, revealing cracks,\" he said.\nThe Russian space agency said a special committee would investigate and determine the cause of the accident.\n\u0421\u0435\u0439\u0447\u0430\u0441\u0447\u0438\u0442\u0430\u044e\u0442","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0036.json.gz:41646","uncompressed_offset":113364068,"url":"cn.inform.kz/amp/article_a3377843/","warc_date":"2023-12-27T21:22:18.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:0a040a3e-2812-41a4-9857-45bdf81b5e75>","warc_url":"https://cn.inform.kz/amp/article_a3377843/"},"created":"2023-12-27T21:28:18.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T146","run_id":"dog","topic_id":"1119","task":"multilingual","request_id":"1119","narrative_id":"1119"},"responses":[{"citations":{"dee4737a-0c59-4e47-b025-e18c6f1cf0bb_287704682":1.0},"text":"The multi-level marketing business model has experienced significant trends in recent years, with some companies experiencing a surge in profits while others have faced a decline."},{"citations":{"dee4737a-0c59-4e47-b025-e18c6f1cf0bb_287704682":1.0},"text":"During the pandemic, companies like Nu Skin Enterprises saw an increase in sales as furloughed workers tried to make ends meet by selling products from home, resulting in the company's stock tripling in value from March 2020 to a June 2021 peak of $62."},{"citations":{"dee4737a-0c59-4e47-b025-e18c6f1cf0bb_287704682":1.0},"text":"However, the pandemic has also posed challenges for some MLM companies, such as Nu Skin, which has been accused of spreading Covid in China, where it generates over 20% of its revenue."},{"citations":{"8dffe6e3-b2e0-4574-97ae-d3a72b383e10_746931846":1.0},"text":"In contrast, other companies have adapted to the pandemic by shifting their focus to online sales and new product offerings, such as Runamok Maple, which saw its online syrup sales skyrocket."},{"citations":{"8dffe6e3-b2e0-4574-97ae-d3a72b383e10_746931846":1.0},"text":"Some MLM companies have also expanded their services to cater to the growing demand for digital solutions, such as LugLess, which partnered with moving companies to reach digital nomads."},{"citations":{"3c29e522-5c23-4b52-88ad-d09ae0ea9bf4_378764971":1.0},"text":"Avon, a former direct selling company, shifted its focus to a multi-level marketing model in 2000, but ultimately experienced a decline in global revenue and stock value, leading to the sale of its North American business."},{"citations":{"3c29e522-5c23-4b52-88ad-d09ae0ea9bf4_378764971":1.0},"text":"The evolution of the direct selling and multi-level marketing business models